2
00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:38.512
1879. The Civil War is over.

3
00:00:38.590 --> 00:00:43.550
and the resulting economic explosion
spurs the great migration west.

4
00:00:43.628 --> 00:00:46.563
Farmers. ranchers. prospectors.
killers and thieves...

5
00:00:46.631 --> 00:00:48.792
seek their fortunes.

6
00:00:48.867 --> 00:00:51.597
Cattle drovers turn cow towns
into armed camps...

7
00:00:51.669 --> 00:00:57.164
with murder rates higher than those
of modern-day New York or Los Angeles.

8
00:00:57.242 --> 00:01:00.678
Out of this chaos comes
legendary lawman Wyatt Earp.

9
00:01:00.745 --> 00:01:04.647
retiring his badge and gun to start
a peaceful life with his family.

10
00:01:04.716 --> 00:01:07.241
Earp's friend
John 'Doc' Holliday...

11
00:01:07.318 --> 00:01:10.082
a Southern gentleman
turned gunman and gambler...

12
00:01:10.155 --> 00:01:15.354
also travels west. hoping the dry
climate will relieve his tuberculosis.

13
00:01:15.427 --> 00:01:17.691
Silver is discovered
in Arizona.

14
00:01:17.762 --> 00:01:20.595
Tombstone becomes
queen of the boomtowns.

15
00:01:20.665 --> 00:01:24.726
where the latest Paris fashions are sold
from the backs of wagons.

16
00:01:24.803 --> 00:01:27.431
Attracted to this
atmosphere of greed.

17
00:01:27.505 --> 00:01:30.167
over 100 exiled Texas outlaws
band together...

18
00:01:30.241 --> 00:01:34.974
to form the ruthless gang recognized
by the red sashes they wear.

19
00:01:35.046 --> 00:01:39.710
They emerge as the earliest example
of organized crime in America.

20
00:01:39.784 --> 00:01:43.311
They call themselves
'The Cowboys'

21
00:03:16.931 --> 00:03:20.594
Y'all killed
two Cowboys.

22
00:03:49.497 --> 00:03:53.160
- �Detenganse!
- Shoot.

23
00:03:53.234 --> 00:03:56.635
- Looks like we win.

24
00:04:10.785 --> 00:04:13.310
Mexican police. huh?

25
00:04:16.724 --> 00:04:20.524
Tell him to get on his knees.

26
00:04:20.595 --> 00:04:23.462
�De rodillas. cabron!

27
00:04:23.531 --> 00:04:26.193
�De rodillas.
dijo. chingada!

28
00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:34.507
He won't no kneel. patron.
He is very proud.

29
00:04:34.575 --> 00:04:37.476
- Hey. somebody get
this dick on his knees.

30
00:04:37.545 --> 00:04:40.105
�Ay. Dios! �Ay. Dios!

31
00:04:40.181 --> 00:04:42.843
Good shot. Billy.

32
00:04:42.917 --> 00:04:47.581
- �Gracias!

33
00:04:49.223 --> 00:04:52.750
They call me
Curly Bill Brosius.

34
00:04:52.827 --> 00:04:57.287
I'm what you might call
the Founder of the Feast.

35
00:04:57.365 --> 00:05:02.302
So next time we come.
you'd better step aside.

36
00:05:04.939 --> 00:05:07.032
I ain't kiddin' neither.

37
00:05:07.108 --> 00:05:10.043
Un caballo bajando
por la montana...

38
00:05:10.111 --> 00:05:13.308
y el que lo cabalgue
ira a la muerte.

39
00:05:13.381 --> 00:05:16.646
�Moriremos!

40
00:05:16.717 --> 00:05:19.345
Patron.
he say. uh.

41
00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:22.412
someone will come
to revenge for him.

42
00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:25.220
Something like a. a... sick horse
who comes to sit with him.

43
00:05:25.293 --> 00:05:27.887
He talk crazy.
No entiendo un carajo.

44
00:05:27.962 --> 00:05:30.829
That's not what he said.
ya ignorant wretch.

45
00:05:30.898 --> 00:05:34.163
Your Spanish is worse
than your English.

46
00:05:36.237 --> 00:05:38.728
You go to hell!

47
00:05:38.806 --> 00:05:42.037
- You first.

48
00:05:42.109 --> 00:05:44.600
- �No!

49
00:05:47.915 --> 00:05:51.510
�No! �No!
- What have we got here?

50
00:06:06.868 --> 00:06:09.769
- Hell. let's eat. boys.
Tamales are good. huh?

51
00:06:09.837 --> 00:06:12.362
I guess they knew
we were comin'.

52
00:06:16.777 --> 00:06:21.077
Temor de Dios. Temor de Dios
es lo que ustedes no tienen.

53
00:06:21.148 --> 00:06:24.049
- �Muerete. hijo de Satanas!

54
00:06:34.595 --> 00:06:37.257
Hey. Johnny. what'd
that Mexican mean...

55
00:06:37.331 --> 00:06:41.631
'a sick horse is
gonna get us.' huh?

56
00:06:41.702 --> 00:06:44.671
He's quoting the Bible.

57
00:06:44.739 --> 00:06:47.833
Revelations.

58
00:06:47.909 --> 00:06:50.605
Behold. a pale horse.

59
00:06:50.678 --> 00:06:54.637
'The man who sat on him
was Death.

60
00:06:54.715 --> 00:06:58.776
And hell followed with him.'

61
00:07:24.946 --> 00:07:28.143
Move!

62
00:07:29.483 --> 00:07:33.442
- Come on! That's it!
You move!

63
00:07:33.521 --> 00:07:36.456
- Stupid mule!

64
00:07:36.524 --> 00:07:38.492
Come on!

65
00:07:38.559 --> 00:07:40.823
Come on!
Come on!

66
00:07:50.338 --> 00:07:52.966
Hurts. don't it?

67
00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:57.739
Now let go of that stud and
go on about your business.

68
00:08:08.889 --> 00:08:12.017
Mr. Earp.
My name's Dake.

69
00:08:12.093 --> 00:08:14.823
Crawley Dake. U.S. Marshal
for this territory.

70
00:08:14.895 --> 00:08:17.728
- Forget it. I'm retired.
- Excuse me?

71
00:08:17.798 --> 00:08:21.290
I said forget it.
I don't want the job. and that's final.

72
00:08:21.369 --> 00:08:24.827
- I don't think you understand.
- No. you don't understand. Marshal.

73
00:08:24.905 --> 00:08:28.932
I did my duty. and now I'd
like to get on with my life.

74
00:08:29.010 --> 00:08:31.638
- I'm going to Tombstone.
Easy on the grain. Butch.
- I see.

75
00:08:31.712 --> 00:08:34.647
- Here you go.
- To strike it rich.
Well. all right. that's fine.

76
00:08:34.715 --> 00:08:37.548
Tell you one thing. though:
Never saw a rich man...

77
00:08:37.618 --> 00:08:40.587
who didn't wind up
with a guilty conscience.

78
00:08:40.654 --> 00:08:45.091
I already got a guilty conscience.
Might as well have the money too.

79
00:08:45.159 --> 00:08:47.923
Good day now.

80
00:08:49.497 --> 00:08:54.560
That's him. all right.
Boy. I'd know that sour face anywhere.

81
00:08:57.805 --> 00:09:00.740
Virgil! Morgan!
My god!

82
00:09:06.313 --> 00:09:08.804
- Hey. boy! How are you. Morgan?
- Hi. Wyatt.

83
00:09:08.883 --> 00:09:11.545
- Well. how do we look?
- Great. both of ya.

84
00:09:11.619 --> 00:09:14.520
- Wyatt. you remember Allie.
- Good God. Well. he'd better.

85
00:09:14.588 --> 00:09:16.681
Allie girl.

86
00:09:16.757 --> 00:09:18.850
- And Louisa. Oh!
- Wyatt.

87
00:09:18.926 --> 00:09:22.020
You're so lovely. darlin'.
I'm at your feet. just at your feet.

88
00:09:22.096 --> 00:09:25.088
I guess it's only right.
Ma always said Morgan's the prettiest.

89
00:09:25.166 --> 00:09:29.125
- Yeah. but she doted on the Frowner.
- That's right.

90
00:09:29.203 --> 00:09:31.569
- Wyatt.
- Mattie!

91
00:09:31.639 --> 00:09:34.699
Mattie. they're already here.
Folks. this is Celia Andon.

92
00:09:34.775 --> 00:09:37.744
- You can call her Mattie.
- Pleased to meet you. Mattie.

93
00:09:37.812 --> 00:09:40.246
It's nice to meet you.

94
00:09:40.314 --> 00:09:43.249
Well. Wyatt. I couldn't
find a single store that
had laudanum anywhere.

95
00:09:43.317 --> 00:09:46.980
That's all right. honey.
I sure been dreamin' about this.

96
00:09:47.054 --> 00:09:50.421
God. since forever!
Wait! Look here.

97
00:09:50.491 --> 00:09:53.426
I wanna...
Look. Huh?

98
00:09:56.497 --> 00:09:58.965
- Hey. Wyatt...
- Don't talk. just...

99
00:09:59.033 --> 00:10:02.093
Yeah.

100
00:10:02.169 --> 00:10:04.569
Thank you for this. Wyatt.

101
00:10:04.638 --> 00:10:08.506
- It's all your doin'.
- We'll make our fortune. boys.

102
00:10:08.576 --> 00:10:10.806
Well. come on.

103
00:10:10.878 --> 00:10:13.447
Gracious.
We could be sisters.

104
00:10:13.580 --> 00:10:16.413
Mighty fine.
I wonder where he found her.

105
00:10:16.483 --> 00:10:19.008
Same place we found ours. probably.

106
00:10:22.489 --> 00:10:25.458
'Matter. honey?
Did you say you needed some laudanum?

107
00:10:25.525 --> 00:10:28.585
- Yes. I did. Yes.
- I have some right here.

108
00:10:28.662 --> 00:10:31.597
Oh. you're a lifesaver.

109
00:10:31.665 --> 00:10:34.600
Just be careful now.
It's full of hop.

110
00:10:34.668 --> 00:10:37.637
Oh. don't worry. I just
get headaches sometimes.

111
00:10:37.704 --> 00:10:40.605
Hey. Virg. see anything of Doc
while you were in Prescott?

112
00:10:40.674 --> 00:10:43.609
Yeah. He had a streak
when we left. him and Kate.

113
00:10:43.677 --> 00:10:46.441
I miss Doc.
I miss that old rip.

114
00:10:46.513 --> 00:10:49.914
- I don't.
- He makes me laugh.

115
00:10:53.253 --> 00:10:55.187
Yeah!

116
00:10:55.288 --> 00:10:59.748
- That's $500. Holliday.
Are you in or out?

117
00:11:08.935 --> 00:11:13.565
Five hundred.
Must be a peach of a hand.

118
00:11:18.712 --> 00:11:20.907
Oh. thank you. darlin'.

119
00:11:20.981 --> 00:11:24.576
Kate! You're not
wearing a bustle.

120
00:11:24.651 --> 00:11:26.846
How lewd.

121
00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:30.754
Come on. Holliday.
you in or out. goddammit?

122
00:11:30.824 --> 00:11:34.419
Why. Ed Bailey. you look like
you're just about ready to burst.

123
00:11:34.494 --> 00:11:38.123
Come on! Come on. show!

124
00:11:38.198 --> 00:11:42.931
Well. I suppose
I'm deranged. but I...

125
00:11:43.003 --> 00:11:45.563
guess I'll just
have to call.

126
00:11:45.639 --> 00:11:48.369
Cover your ears. darlin'.

127
00:11:51.111 --> 00:11:53.136
Isn't that a daisy?

128
00:11:53.213 --> 00:11:56.239
Why. you son-of-a-bitch!

129
00:11:56.316 --> 00:11:58.284
Damn. Bailey. just settle down!

130
00:11:58.351 --> 00:12:02.447
Shut up! Take your
money and get out.

131
00:12:02.522 --> 00:12:05.150
'cause I'm tired of
listenin' to your mouth.

132
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:08.194
Why. Ed Bailey.

133
00:12:08.261 --> 00:12:10.752
are we cross?

134
00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:14.425
Them guns don't scare me.

135
00:12:14.501 --> 00:12:18.801
'Cause without them guns
you ain't nothin' but a skinny lunger.

136
00:12:18.872 --> 00:12:22.273
Ed. what an ugly thing to say.

137
00:12:22.342 --> 00:12:27.245
- I abhor ugliness. Does this
mean we're not friends anymore?
-

138
00:12:27.314 --> 00:12:30.943
You know. Ed. if I thought
you weren't my friend.

139
00:12:31.017 --> 00:12:34.111
I just don't think
I could bear it.

140
00:12:51.237 --> 00:12:54.604
There. Now we can
be friends again.

141
00:13:06.353 --> 00:13:09.220
- Touch that gun.
I'll burn you down.

142
00:13:18.198 --> 00:13:21.133
I calculate that's
the end of this town.

143
00:13:21.201 --> 00:13:25.695
I had a boy at the hotel pack us up.
The horse is outside.

144
00:13:25.772 --> 00:13:28.900
So that's why you're
not wearin' a bustle.

145
00:13:31.711 --> 00:13:35.010
My sweet. soft
Hungarian devil.

146
00:13:39.653 --> 00:13:42.588
Well!

147
00:13:45.959 --> 00:13:48.985
Good evenin'. then.

148
00:13:52.666 --> 00:13:55.601
Let's not bother
about the luggage.

149
00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:44.073
Hyah!

150
00:15:18.618 --> 00:15:21.815
Hey. Morg.
pretty big. isn't it?

151
00:15:25.024 --> 00:15:30.189
Oh-ho. brother. you can smell
the silver in this town.

152
00:15:30.263 --> 00:15:33.255
- Easy.
- Look at these girls over here.

153
00:15:33.333 --> 00:15:36.427
- Hi!
- Hello. girls!

154
00:15:36.503 --> 00:15:38.937
Hot damn. this burg's jumpin'!

155
00:15:39.005 --> 00:15:41.496
Here we go. ladies.

156
00:15:41.574 --> 00:15:45.772
- Isn't that sweet?
- You can say that.

157
00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:55.948
- Sheriff.

158
00:16:04.597 --> 00:16:06.963
Newcomers. eh?

159
00:16:07.033 --> 00:16:10.366
The name's John Behan.
Cochise County Sheriff.

160
00:16:10.436 --> 00:16:12.700
- Just in town?
- Just this minute.

161
00:16:12.772 --> 00:16:17.141
- I'm Wyatt Earp. and these are
my brothers. Virgil and Morgan.
- Wyatt Earp. Dodge City.

162
00:16:17.210 --> 00:16:20.373
Gave all that up. Sheriff.
Goin' into business.

163
00:16:20.446 --> 00:16:24.780
- Don't even carry a gun anymore.
- Going into business. huh?

164
00:16:24.851 --> 00:16:27.547
Well then. I'm the man to see.

165
00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:30.088
Besides sheriff.
I'm also tax collector.

166
00:16:30.156 --> 00:16:33.557
Captain of the Fire Brigade and Chairman
of the Nonpartisan Anti-Chinese League.

167
00:16:33.626 --> 00:16:36.026
- Ma'am.
- How do you do?

168
00:16:37.630 --> 00:16:40.098
Yeah. a man of many parts.

169
00:16:40.166 --> 00:16:43.602
- Say. you folks got
a place to stay yet?
- No.

170
00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:47.333
- Like I said. we just got here.
- Well. I also sit on
the town lot commission.

171
00:16:47.407 --> 00:16:49.705
Really?

172
00:16:49.776 --> 00:16:54.679
As a matter of fact. we got three
lovely cottages coming up for rent.

173
00:16:54.747 --> 00:16:57.773
I'll throw in a good cleaning.
no charge.

174
00:16:57.851 --> 00:16:59.944
Believe me. Mr. Earp.

175
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:03.284
you're not gonna find a better deal
within town limits.

176
00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:05.790
I don't know.
sounds pretty good.

177
00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:09.727
- Well. I'll have my man show 'em to ya.
- Thank you.

178
00:17:16.102 --> 00:17:19.538
Hey. Wyatt.
get on over here.

179
00:17:19.606 --> 00:17:22.439
I want you to meet Fred White.
He's the town marshall.

180
00:17:22.508 --> 00:17:24.703
- My pleasure.
- Lotta law around here.

181
00:17:24.777 --> 00:17:27.769
- I already met the county sheriff.
- Who. Behan?

182
00:17:27.847 --> 00:17:31.681
He ain't no law. The only real law
around here is the Cowboys.

183
00:17:31.751 --> 00:17:35.915
Cowboys? I had a run-in
with a couple of them up in Prescott.

184
00:17:35.989 --> 00:17:39.083
Nobody does nothin' without 'em.
I mean. they're it.

185
00:17:39.158 --> 00:17:41.718
There are three of 'em
right over there.

186
00:17:41.794 --> 00:17:46.163
You can always spot a Cowboy.
They always wear those red sashes.

187
00:17:46.232 --> 00:17:50.100
- The main fact is the Cowboys
are good for business.
- 'Bout all these saloons?

188
00:17:50.169 --> 00:17:53.229
Oh. that's the real mother lode
here in Tombstone.

189
00:17:53.306 --> 00:17:55.740
All up and down
Allen Street here.

190
00:17:55.808 --> 00:17:58.606
Twenty-four hours a day.
you got liquor. hostesses. gamblin';

191
00:17:58.678 --> 00:18:01.078
makin' money
hand-over-fist.

192
00:18:01.147 --> 00:18:05.447
All except 'the Oriental.'
That's a regular slaughterhouse.

193
00:18:05.518 --> 00:18:08.453
Even the high rollers
won't go near it.

194
00:18:08.521 --> 00:18:12.514
That's too bad too.
It's a nice place.

195
00:18:12.592 --> 00:18:15.459
Hell of a waste.

196
00:18:15.528 --> 00:18:18.361
- Wyatt?

197
00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:20.661
- There he goes.
- Yeah.

198
00:18:22.902 --> 00:18:26.030
OI' Wyatt.

199
00:18:29.576 --> 00:18:32.511
All right. fella.
I'll brace ya now for a little lesson.

200
00:18:32.579 --> 00:18:36.106
Put your money on the board.
Five dollars on that six of spades.

201
00:18:36.183 --> 00:18:38.743
Like that.

202
00:18:38.819 --> 00:18:43.188
I'm not gonna tell you again.
Get that cigar outta my face.

203
00:18:43.256 --> 00:18:45.884
Howdy. stranger.
What can I get ya?

204
00:18:45.959 --> 00:18:48.120
I wouldn't mind
one of those cigars.

205
00:18:48.195 --> 00:18:50.857
I'm about ready to go home.
I wish y'all would stop yakkin'...

206
00:18:50.931 --> 00:18:53.058
- and just play cards.
- Thank you.

207
00:18:53.133 --> 00:18:56.068
Kinda nice in here.
You run it?

208
00:18:56.136 --> 00:18:58.331
Milt Joyce: Owner. operator.

209
00:18:58.405 --> 00:19:01.841
- Wyatt Earp.
- Yeah. sure.

210
00:19:01.908 --> 00:19:04.638
I said lay off the queen.
you jackass!

211
00:19:04.711 --> 00:19:07.578
I swear I'm gonna
slap somebody now.

212
00:19:07.647 --> 00:19:12.812
Excuse me for askin'. Milt.
but... kinda dead in here. isn't it?

213
00:19:12.886 --> 00:19:15.753
- You don't listen too good. do ya?
- See that bird at the faro table?

214
00:19:15.822 --> 00:19:18.985
You back that queen again.
you son-of-a-bitch.

215
00:19:19.059 --> 00:19:22.153
I'll blow you right up
that wildcat's ass!
Do you hear me. huh?

216
00:19:22.229 --> 00:19:26.131
He comes bargin' in here one day.
slappin' the customers.
wavin' his gun around.

217
00:19:26.199 --> 00:19:28.633
He chased out all
the high-class play.

218
00:19:28.702 --> 00:19:32.695
The only trade that comes in
here now is the bummers and
the drovers; just the dregs.

219
00:19:32.772 --> 00:19:36.367
Why don't you get rid of him.
get yourself a straight dealer?

220
00:19:36.443 --> 00:19:38.741
Sure. stranger.
that's easy for you to say.

221
00:19:38.812 --> 00:19:41.713
Shit!

222
00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:45.782
Goddammit. Junior. how many times
am I going to tell you...

223
00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:50.949
to keep that damn cigar
outta my face? Huh?

224
00:19:51.024 --> 00:19:54.983
Christ almighty. it's like I'm
sittin' here playing cards with
my brother's kids or somethin'.

225
00:19:55.061 --> 00:19:57.393
you nerve-wracking
sons-of-bitches.

226
00:19:59.933 --> 00:20:01.924
Is somethin' on your mind?

227
00:20:02.002 --> 00:20:04.937
Just want to let you know
you're sittin' in my chair.

228
00:20:05.005 --> 00:20:07.405
Is that a fact?

229
00:20:07.474 --> 00:20:09.908
Yeah. it's a fact.

230
00:20:09.976 --> 00:20:13.935
For a man that don't go heeled. you run
your mouth kinda reckless. don't ya?

231
00:20:14.014 --> 00:20:17.950
No need to go heeled to get
the bulge on a tub like you.

232
00:20:18.018 --> 00:20:20.885
- Is that a fact?
- Mm-hmm.

233
00:20:20.954 --> 00:20:23.718
That's a fact.

234
00:20:25.292 --> 00:20:28.284
Well. I'm real scared.

235
00:20:28.361 --> 00:20:33.230
Damn right. you're scared.
I can see that in your eyes.

236
00:20:33.300 --> 00:20:35.791
- All right now!
- Go ahead.

237
00:20:35.869 --> 00:20:39.965
Go ahead. skin it! Skin that
smoke wagon and see what happens.

238
00:20:42.509 --> 00:20:45.307
Listen. mister.
l-I'm gettin' awful tired of your...

239
00:20:45.378 --> 00:20:48.643
I'm gettin' tired of your gas.
Now jerk that pistol and go to work.

240
00:20:51.051 --> 00:20:55.420
- I said throw down. boy.

241
00:21:01.962 --> 00:21:05.898
You gonna do somethin'.
or just stand there and bleed?

242
00:21:08.835 --> 00:21:11.133
No?

243
00:21:13.406 --> 00:21:15.840
I didn't think so.

244
00:21:15.909 --> 00:21:19.743
Here. Milt. a keepsake.

245
00:21:21.481 --> 00:21:25.349
Hang it over the bar.
All right. youngster. out you go.

246
00:21:27.587 --> 00:21:30.147
Don't come back!

247
00:21:30.223 --> 00:21:32.657
Ever!

248
00:21:36.229 --> 00:21:38.595
Well. what do you say. Milt?

249
00:21:38.665 --> 00:21:42.157
Twenty-five percent
of the house take sound about right?

250
00:21:42.235 --> 00:21:44.669
Hyah!

251
00:21:48.608 --> 00:21:51.543
Well. we're off and runnin'.

252
00:21:51.611 --> 00:21:54.842
Just acquired us a quarter interest
in a game at 'the Oriental.'

253
00:21:54.914 --> 00:21:57.109
- Acquired?
- So to speak.

254
00:22:00.987 --> 00:22:03.581
Now all we gotta do is keep our
eyes on that brass ring. fellas.

255
00:22:03.657 --> 00:22:06.353
You're the one. Wyatt.

256
00:22:06.426 --> 00:22:09.759
Why. Johnny Tyler!

257
00:22:09.829 --> 00:22:12.821
- You madcap!
- Doc?

258
00:22:12.899 --> 00:22:16.266
Where you goin'
with that shotgun?

259
00:22:16.336 --> 00:22:19.669
I didn't know you
was back in town.

260
00:22:21.508 --> 00:22:23.703
Well. well.

261
00:22:23.777 --> 00:22:26.940
How the hell are you?

262
00:22:27.013 --> 00:22:30.972
Wyatt. I am rolling.
Morgan.

263
00:22:31.051 --> 00:22:33.815
- Doc.
- Virgil.

264
00:22:33.887 --> 00:22:36.651
'Lo. Doc.

265
00:22:36.723 --> 00:22:39.248
Wyatt Earp?

266
00:22:42.796 --> 00:22:46.129
Going into business
for ourselves. Doc.

267
00:22:46.199 --> 00:22:49.532
- Wyatt just got us a faro game.
- Oh.

268
00:22:49.602 --> 00:22:52.196
Since when is faro
a business?

269
00:22:52.272 --> 00:22:55.673
- Didn't you always say that
gambling's an honest trade?
- No.

270
00:22:55.742 --> 00:23:00.076
I said poker's an honest trade.
Only suckers buck the tiger's
odds all on the house.

271
00:23:00.146 --> 00:23:04.344
Depends on how you look at it.
I mean. it's not like anybody's
puttin' a gun to their head.

272
00:23:04.417 --> 00:23:08.820
That's what I love about Wyatt.
He can talk himself into anything.

273
00:23:10.924 --> 00:23:14.985
Oh. Johnny. I apologize.
I forgot you were there.

274
00:23:15.061 --> 00:23:17.325
You may go now.

275
00:23:17.397 --> 00:23:20.889
Just leave that shotgun.

276
00:23:24.537 --> 00:23:27.335
Leave it.

277
00:23:28.575 --> 00:23:31.169
Thank you.

278
00:23:32.579 --> 00:23:35.241
Sheriff Behan!

279
00:23:35.315 --> 00:23:38.284
- Gentlemen!
- Sheriff.

280
00:23:38.351 --> 00:23:42.014
- have you met Doc Holliday?
- Piss on you. Wyatt.

281
00:23:43.256 --> 00:23:46.419
Mr. Holliday.

282
00:23:46.493 --> 00:23:49.860
Forgive me
if I don't shake hands.

283
00:23:52.699 --> 00:23:55.429
- So. how's our little town suit you?
- Fine. Fine.

284
00:23:55.502 --> 00:23:59.199
You know. I was thinking. what this town
could really use is a racetrack.

285
00:23:59.272 --> 00:24:03.504
Really? That's not a bad idea.
Send a signal we're growin' up.

286
00:24:03.576 --> 00:24:07.637
Way ahead of yourselves.
aren't you. boys? This
is just another mining camp.

287
00:24:07.714 --> 00:24:11.275
Have you seen how everyone dresses?
Awful tony for a mining camp.

288
00:24:11.351 --> 00:24:13.785
No sir. the die is cast.
We are growin'.

289
00:24:13.853 --> 00:24:17.380
- Be as big as San Francisco in
a few years. and just as sophisticated.

290
00:24:17.457 --> 00:24:21.416
- You son-of-a-bitch!

291
00:24:21.494 --> 00:24:23.985
Easy. gents!
It's a private affair!

292
00:24:24.063 --> 00:24:29.023
- Don't raise that iron.
I'm gonna have to...
- I'll kill you. you cheap son-of-a...

293
00:24:30.970 --> 00:24:34.667
Very cosmopolitan.

294
00:24:34.741 --> 00:24:37.369
I know him.
That's Creek Johnson.

295
00:24:40.747 --> 00:24:43.113
Wyatt? Doc?

296
00:24:44.584 --> 00:24:48.543
- Jack.
- What do you say. old friend?

297
00:24:49.789 --> 00:24:52.758
What the hell's that
all about. Creek?

298
00:24:52.826 --> 00:24:56.125
- He crawfished a bet
and called me a liar.
- Sheriff.

299
00:24:56.196 --> 00:25:00.565
may I present a pair
of fellow sophisticates:
Turkey Creek Jack Johnson.

300
00:25:00.633 --> 00:25:02.658
Texas Jack Vermillion.

301
00:25:02.735 --> 00:25:06.296
Watch your ear. Creek.

302
00:25:06.372 --> 00:25:09.933
- Afraid I'll have to have those guns.
- It was a fair fight.

303
00:25:10.009 --> 00:25:13.445
- We was legal.
- I'm sorry. boys. I gotta
take 'em before Judge Spicer.

304
00:25:13.513 --> 00:25:16.038
Hand 'em over.

305
00:25:16.115 --> 00:25:18.413
Law and order every time.
that's us.

306
00:25:21.888 --> 00:25:25.153
- Ha!

307
00:25:28.928 --> 00:25:31.863
Whoa!

308
00:25:33.366 --> 00:25:35.664
I'm frightfully thirsty.

309
00:25:35.735 --> 00:25:38.670
Well. we made it.

310
00:25:43.443 --> 00:25:46.276
Sheriff.
what kinda town is this?

311
00:25:49.616 --> 00:25:52.414
Nice scenery.

312
00:25:56.956 --> 00:25:59.823
Well.

313
00:25:59.893 --> 00:26:02.953
an enchanted moment.

314
00:26:07.901 --> 00:26:12.304
Interesting little scene. I wonder
who that tall drink of water is.

315
00:26:12.372 --> 00:26:16.103
My dear. you have set your gaze
upon the quintessential frontier type.

316
00:26:16.175 --> 00:26:20.236
Note the lean silhouette. eyes closed
by the sun; they're sharp as a hawk.

317
00:26:20.313 --> 00:26:24.682
He's got the look of
both predator... and prey.

318
00:26:24.751 --> 00:26:27.083
I want one.

319
00:26:27.153 --> 00:26:29.747
Happy hunting.

320
00:26:57.717 --> 00:27:00.015
- Hey. sister boy. gimme some!

321
00:27:00.086 --> 00:27:03.249
- Gimme. gimme. gimme!
- Leave him alone. Barnes!

322
00:27:03.323 --> 00:27:06.224
Billy. sit with me.

323
00:27:13.032 --> 00:27:16.934
This is so much fun. We haven't
been to the show in six years.

324
00:27:17.003 --> 00:27:19.631
I hope they're good.

325
00:27:21.941 --> 00:27:24.603
- Wyatt?
- Oh. sorry.

326
00:27:28.014 --> 00:27:31.381
Darlin'. you know the Earps.

327
00:27:31.451 --> 00:27:33.646
Kate. how you been?

328
00:27:35.188 --> 00:27:38.055
Mattie. hmm. ravishin'.

329
00:27:38.124 --> 00:27:40.649
Doc.

330
00:27:42.362 --> 00:27:45.991
Wyatt. I'd like ya
to meet Mayor Clum and his wife.

331
00:27:46.065 --> 00:27:49.000
- Mr. Earp.
Your reputation precedes you.
- Mayor.

332
00:27:49.068 --> 00:27:53.164
- I was wondering if you might be...
- Not a prayer. Nice meetin' you.

333
00:28:06.052 --> 00:28:10.785
Professor Gillman? Oh. I seen him
in Bisbee. He catches stuff.

334
00:28:10.857 --> 00:28:13.348
Hey. Professor.
catch this.

335
00:28:15.428 --> 00:28:18.192
They're shooting at us!
They're actually shooting at us.

336
00:28:18.264 --> 00:28:22.200
- I guess we'll have
to wait for our notices.

337
00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:27.203
Prettiest man I ever saw.

338
00:28:27.273 --> 00:28:29.002
Whoo!

339
00:28:29.075 --> 00:28:31.669
- Whoo-hoo!
- Ladies and gentlemen.

340
00:28:31.744 --> 00:28:34.406
the St. Crispin's Day
speech from Henry V.

341
00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:37.415
- To set the scene...

342
00:28:37.483 --> 00:28:39.644
Goddamn. Barnes!
- Shot his damn ear off.

343
00:28:39.719 --> 00:28:42.483
- 'Lf we are marked to die.

344
00:28:42.555 --> 00:28:44.989
'we are now to do
our country loss.

345
00:28:45.058 --> 00:28:50.155
But if to live. the fewer men.
the greater share of honor... '

346
00:28:50.229 --> 00:28:53.426
He's got some nerve. I'll say that.
What d'ya think there. Billy Nilly?

347
00:28:53.499 --> 00:28:57.333
- I think he's wonderful.

348
00:28:57.403 --> 00:28:59.371
'... gentle his condition.

349
00:28:59.439 --> 00:29:02.897
'Gentlemen in England now abed
shall think themselves accurs'd
they were not here.

350
00:29:02.976 --> 00:29:06.878
- 'And hold their manhoods cheap...

351
00:29:06.946 --> 00:29:11.280
whilst any speaks who fought with us
upon Saint Crispin's day.'

352
00:29:11.351 --> 00:29:14.184
- That's great!
That's our kinda stuff!

353
00:29:22.195 --> 00:29:24.595
Play it again!

354
00:29:34.007 --> 00:29:36.874
Now what in the hell is this?

355
00:29:36.943 --> 00:29:41.937
Th-That's Faust.
H-He's gonna make a deal with the devil.

356
00:29:42.015 --> 00:29:45.314
Is your soul
for sale. dear?

357
00:29:59.298 --> 00:30:01.732
Know what I'd do?

358
00:30:01.801 --> 00:30:05.430
I'd take the deal. then crawfish
and drill that old devil in the ass.

359
00:30:08.141 --> 00:30:11.577
How 'bout you. Juanito?
What would you do?

360
00:30:13.112 --> 00:30:16.741
I already did it.

361
00:30:34.934 --> 00:30:37.960
Very instructive.

362
00:30:39.372 --> 00:30:42.603
- Hmm.

363
00:30:43.910 --> 00:30:46.276
But who is the devil?

364
00:30:58.925 --> 00:31:01.416
I'll be damned.

365
00:31:02.729 --> 00:31:05.596
You may indeed.
if you get lucky.

366
00:31:09.936 --> 00:31:12.871
Would you look
at all those stars?

367
00:31:12.939 --> 00:31:17.137
I mean. you look up and you think.
'God made all of that?

368
00:31:17.210 --> 00:31:20.771
He still remembered to make
a little speck like me.'

369
00:31:20.847 --> 00:31:23.782
Kinda flattering.
really.

370
00:31:23.850 --> 00:31:26.580
Wyatt. do you
believe in God?

371
00:31:26.652 --> 00:31:29.678
- No. come on. really. Do ya?
- Yeah. Maybe.

372
00:31:29.756 --> 00:31:33.021
- Hell. I don't know.
- Well. what d'you think
happens when you die?

373
00:31:33.092 --> 00:31:35.856
Somethin'. Nothin'.
Hell. I don't know.

374
00:31:35.928 --> 00:31:38.829
Well. I read this book.
a book on spiritualism.

375
00:31:38.898 --> 00:31:41.366
Oh. God. here
he goes again.

376
00:31:41.434 --> 00:31:44.369
Said that a lot of people
when they die. they see this light.

377
00:31:44.437 --> 00:31:46.871
- Like in a tunnel.
- Yeah?

378
00:31:46.939 --> 00:31:49.874
- They say it's the light
leadin' you to Heaven.
- Really?

379
00:31:49.942 --> 00:31:53.503
- Well. what about Hell?
They got a sign there. or what?
- Hey. Wyatt. goddammit.

380
00:31:53.579 --> 00:31:57.015
- I'm serious.
- Hey. Morg. Comin'
to the Oriental. Virg?

381
00:31:57.083 --> 00:31:59.381
- Well...
- Not tonight.

382
00:31:59.452 --> 00:32:02.319
Tonight. me and my old man
are gonna have some fun.

383
00:32:02.388 --> 00:32:04.652
Come on. get movin'.
old man.

384
00:32:04.724 --> 00:32:07.659
Maiden name was Sullivan.

385
00:32:09.729 --> 00:32:15.133
- Well. you better go with them.
honey. I gotta go to work.
- Please stay with me.

386
00:32:15.201 --> 00:32:18.693
Well. honey. l-I
gotta get to work.

387
00:32:18.771 --> 00:32:21.968
All right.
All right.

388
00:32:22.041 --> 00:32:25.442
Well. wait a minute. I guess
I don't have to go right now. I...

389
00:32:25.511 --> 00:32:28.503
- I could stay awhile.
- No. no. I don't wanna keep you.

390
00:32:28.581 --> 00:32:31.106
No. really.
I can stay awhile.

391
00:32:31.184 --> 00:32:35.814
That the bottle
Lou gave you?

392
00:32:35.888 --> 00:32:38.322
Yes. it is.

393
00:32:38.391 --> 00:32:40.655
Maybe you should
see a doctor.

394
00:32:43.095 --> 00:32:45.529
Wyatt. it's
just headaches.

395
00:32:45.598 --> 00:32:48.965
I know what I'm doing. No.
I don't need to see a doctor!

396
00:32:49.035 --> 00:32:51.595
- All right. honey. Okay.
- Just go.

397
00:32:51.671 --> 00:32:54.538
Everything's fine. Wyatt.

398
00:32:54.607 --> 00:32:57.701
- Work well.
- All right. good night.

399
00:32:59.912 --> 00:33:02.745
You look beautiful tonight.

400
00:33:02.815 --> 00:33:05.443
Thank you.

401
00:33:08.054 --> 00:33:10.989
- Night. Mattie.
- Good night. Morgan.

402
00:33:13.726 --> 00:33:15.956
Come on.

403
00:33:19.699 --> 00:33:22.896
- I want to match
seven. seven stinkin' spades.

404
00:33:22.969 --> 00:33:25.403
- Let's go.
- I'm your man.

405
00:33:25.471 --> 00:33:28.440
You win again. Well played. sir.
You are on fire.

406
00:33:28.507 --> 00:33:31.169
- I told you. I'm burnin' up tonight.
- Loser on the ace.

407
00:33:31.244 --> 00:33:34.179
I'll take the red seven.
and I got some deeds here.

408
00:33:34.247 --> 00:33:37.842
- I'll take seven stinkin' diamonds.
- Awww-ful lot of money.

409
00:33:37.917 --> 00:33:41.182
- You can't stand the heat. pal.
get out of the kitchen.
- You're the doctor.

410
00:33:41.254 --> 00:33:43.586
Sad news. friend.
you lose.

411
00:33:43.656 --> 00:33:47.387
- So. now we're in
the mining business.
- You're the one. Wyatt.

412
00:33:47.460 --> 00:33:50.054
We're turnin' into
regular tycoons.

413
00:33:50.129 --> 00:33:53.428
Think I'll call this one
the Mattie Blalock. Mattie'd
get a kick outta that one.

414
00:33:53.499 --> 00:33:56.127
- That's her maiden name.
- And what a maiden.

415
00:33:56.202 --> 00:33:59.137
- Pure as the driven snow. I'm sure.
- Hey. Doc. come on now.

416
00:33:59.205 --> 00:34:02.663
It's just his style. Morg.
He doesn't mean anything.

417
00:34:02.742 --> 00:34:05.370
Tell me something.
my friend. I'm curious.

418
00:34:05.444 --> 00:34:09.847
Do you actually consider yourself
a married man. forsaking all others?

419
00:34:09.916 --> 00:34:12.077
Yeah. pretty much.

420
00:34:12.151 --> 00:34:16.019
I mean. I was no angel
when we met. but neither was she.

421
00:34:16.088 --> 00:34:20.548
People can change. Doc.
Sooner or later. you gotta grow up.

422
00:34:20.626 --> 00:34:22.992
I see.

423
00:34:23.062 --> 00:34:26.828
And what would you do.
if she walked in here?

424
00:34:26.899 --> 00:34:31.359
- 'She'?
- You know damn well who I mean.

425
00:34:31.437 --> 00:34:34.201
That dusky-hued
lady satan. that's who.

426
00:34:34.273 --> 00:34:36.537
- Oh. I'd probably ignore her.
- Ignore her?

427
00:34:36.609 --> 00:34:39.544
I'd ignore her.
People can change. Doc.

428
00:34:39.612 --> 00:34:41.978
I'll remember
you said that.

429
00:34:42.048 --> 00:34:44.380
- What?

430
00:34:47.353 --> 00:34:51.255
- Bravo! Bravo!
- Ma'am? Miss Marcus?

431
00:34:51.324 --> 00:34:54.054
Aw. hell.

432
00:34:56.929 --> 00:34:58.920
Bravo!

433
00:35:10.910 --> 00:35:13.037
Whoo!

434
00:35:17.917 --> 00:35:21.114
Miss Marcus. allow me
the pleasure of a drink.

435
00:35:21.187 --> 00:35:24.156
- Thank you. sir.
- Milt. champagne!

436
00:35:24.223 --> 00:35:26.316
Satisfied?

437
00:35:26.392 --> 00:35:29.987
I stand corrected. Wyatt.
You're an oak.

438
00:35:41.440 --> 00:35:44.375
- Thanks. Kate.

439
00:35:52.885 --> 00:35:55.217
Mr. Fabian.

440
00:35:55.288 --> 00:35:57.119
- Well done.
- Well done.

441
00:35:57.190 --> 00:35:59.158
Good show. partner.
good show.

442
00:35:59.225 --> 00:36:01.785
Mr. Fabian. would you
come sit at my table?

443
00:36:03.396 --> 00:36:06.332
Mr. Earp. would you mind signing
an autograph for me. sir?

444
00:36:06.332 --> 00:36:07.663
Mr. Earp. would you mind signing
an autograph for me. sir?

445
00:36:07.733 --> 00:36:12.067
My wife's not gonna
believe this.

446
00:36:16.108 --> 00:36:19.669
Wyatt Earp. huh?
Heard of you.

447
00:36:21.113 --> 00:36:24.378
Listen now.
Mr. Kansas Law Dog.

448
00:36:24.450 --> 00:36:27.510
Law don't go around here.
Savvy?

449
00:36:27.587 --> 00:36:30.522
- I'm retired.
- Good.

450
00:36:30.590 --> 00:36:33.388
That's real good.

451
00:36:33.459 --> 00:36:37.896
Yeah. Yeah. that's real good. law dog.
'cause law just don't go around here.

452
00:36:37.964 --> 00:36:41.730
Yeah. I heard you the first
time. Winner to the king.
Five hundred dollars.

453
00:36:45.972 --> 00:36:50.739
- Shut up. Ike.
- You must be Doc Holliday.

454
00:36:50.810 --> 00:36:53.711
That's the rumor.

455
00:36:53.779 --> 00:36:57.613
You retired too?

456
00:36:57.683 --> 00:37:00.846
Not me.
I'm in my prime.

457
00:37:00.920 --> 00:37:03.912
Yeah. you look it.

458
00:37:03.990 --> 00:37:08.484
- Uh. you must be Ringo.

459
00:37:08.561 --> 00:37:11.462
Look. darlin'.
Johnny Ringo.

460
00:37:11.530 --> 00:37:16.524
the deadliest pistoleer
since Wild Bill. they say.

461
00:37:16.602 --> 00:37:20.402
What do you think. darlin'.
should I hate him?

462
00:37:20.473 --> 00:37:23.704
- You don't even know him.
- No. That's true.

463
00:37:23.776 --> 00:37:27.735
but... I don't know. there's
just somethin' about him.

464
00:37:27.813 --> 00:37:31.112
Somethin' 'round the eyes.

465
00:37:31.183 --> 00:37:34.277
I don't know.

466
00:37:34.353 --> 00:37:37.584
Reminds me of...

467
00:37:37.657 --> 00:37:40.057
me.

468
00:37:40.126 --> 00:37:43.527
No. I'm sure of it.
I hate him.

469
00:37:43.596 --> 00:37:45.894
He's drunk.

470
00:37:45.965 --> 00:37:48.763
In vino veritas.

471
00:37:48.834 --> 00:37:53.203
Age quod agis.

472
00:38:05.318 --> 00:38:08.082
In pace requiescat.

473
00:38:08.154 --> 00:38:13.114
Come on. boys. we don't want any
trouble in here. not in any language.

474
00:38:13.192 --> 00:38:15.422
That's Latin. darlin'.

475
00:38:15.494 --> 00:38:18.657
Evidently. Mr. Ringo's
an educated man.

476
00:38:18.731 --> 00:38:21.256
Now I really hate him.

477
00:38:22.368 --> 00:38:25.826
- Watch it. Johnny.

478
00:38:25.905 --> 00:38:28.965
- I hear he's real fast.

479
00:38:36.349 --> 00:38:39.284
- Come on. Go. Johnny.

480
00:38:59.105 --> 00:39:02.199
- Yeah!

481
00:39:42.014 --> 00:39:43.675
- Bravo!

482
00:39:52.992 --> 00:39:55.256
- Drinks are on me!
- Whoo!

483
00:40:02.168 --> 00:40:04.693
Gettin' kinda spooky
around here.

484
00:40:04.770 --> 00:40:07.204
- Curly Bill. huh?
- Mm-hmm.

485
00:40:07.273 --> 00:40:11.073
- Who was that other idiot?
- Ike Clanton.

486
00:40:11.143 --> 00:40:14.943
- Table's open!
- The man dealing faro. who is he?

487
00:40:15.014 --> 00:40:20.281
That's Wyatt Earp. Built a name for
himself as a peace officer in Kansas.

488
00:40:20.352 --> 00:40:23.617
Hmm. peace officer.

489
00:40:23.689 --> 00:40:26.123
Very impressive.

490
00:40:28.294 --> 00:40:31.058
I believe he's married.

491
00:40:33.365 --> 00:40:35.458
More champagne?

492
00:40:52.384 --> 00:40:55.319
Oh. hell.

493
00:41:03.162 --> 00:41:06.359
- Hello.
- Hello.

494
00:41:06.432 --> 00:41:09.094
We've. uh. we've never actually met.
My name is...

495
00:41:09.168 --> 00:41:11.363
Wyatt Earp.
Yes. I know.

496
00:41:11.437 --> 00:41:13.701
- I'm Jos...
- Josephine Marcus.

497
00:41:13.772 --> 00:41:16.240
Everybody knows.

498
00:41:17.443 --> 00:41:20.207
I was beginning to think
we'd never meet.

499
00:41:20.279 --> 00:41:23.476
This is fortuitous.
That means 'lucky.'

500
00:41:23.549 --> 00:41:26.211
Yeah. I...
I know what it means.

501
00:41:26.285 --> 00:41:28.480
- Easy now.

502
00:41:28.554 --> 00:41:31.455
- What is it?
- That mare is in season.

503
00:41:31.524 --> 00:41:34.891
Bet she's starting.

504
00:41:34.960 --> 00:41:39.624
- How do they know?
- They know. It's the scent.

505
00:41:39.698 --> 00:41:41.563
Ah!

506
00:41:43.469 --> 00:41:46.666
- Well. I guess we'd better split
'em up. It's been real n...
- I have a better idea.

507
00:41:46.739 --> 00:41:48.969
Let's run it out of them.

508
00:41:51.577 --> 00:41:54.045
Yeah. I'm an oak.
all right.

509
00:42:34.186 --> 00:42:37.121
- Whoa!

510
00:42:37.189 --> 00:42:40.124
Well. end of the road.

511
00:42:40.192 --> 00:42:42.717
- Maybe for you. Hyah!
- Hyah!

512
00:43:03.082 --> 00:43:05.380
That was lovely.

513
00:43:05.451 --> 00:43:08.477
Lovely? You could've been
killed back there. or busted up.

514
00:43:08.554 --> 00:43:10.681
Fun. though.
wasn't it?

515
00:43:10.756 --> 00:43:13.691
- You'd die for fun?
- Wouldn't you?

516
00:43:15.928 --> 00:43:18.692
Oh. he's laughing. I didn't
think you ever laughed.

517
00:43:18.764 --> 00:43:21.130
Yeah. I...
I laugh sometimes.

518
00:43:21.200 --> 00:43:24.002
Yes. but how often?
Are you happy?

519
00:43:24.135 --> 00:43:29.072
Am I happy? Well. I don't know.
I'm happy as the next man. I guess.

520
00:43:29.140 --> 00:43:32.132
I don't laugh all day long like
an idiot. if that's what you mean.

521
00:43:32.210 --> 00:43:35.441
- Touchy about it. aren't you?
- No. I'm not touchy. I'm just...

522
00:43:35.513 --> 00:43:40.143
It's a silly question. is all.
'Am I happy? Are you happy? '
Are you happy?

523
00:43:40.218 --> 00:43:43.278
Oh. I'm always happy.
unless I'm bored.

524
00:43:43.354 --> 00:43:46.289
That blonde woman.
is that your wife?

525
00:43:47.392 --> 00:43:49.826
What about her?

526
00:43:49.894 --> 00:43:53.830
Nothing. What do you
want out of life?

527
00:43:55.466 --> 00:43:57.900
Geez!

528
00:43:57.969 --> 00:44:00.631
- How do you get these questions?
- Just answer.

529
00:44:00.705 --> 00:44:03.139
I don't know!
Make some money. I guess.

530
00:44:03.207 --> 00:44:06.768
- Maybe... have some children.
- Doesn't suit you.

531
00:44:06.844 --> 00:44:10.678
- Well. how would you know?
- It just doesn't. that's all.

532
00:44:10.748 --> 00:44:14.514
I oughta know my own mind.
and I'm telling you what
suits me is a family and kids.

533
00:44:14.585 --> 00:44:17.554
Suits me right down to the ground.
In fact. that's my idea of heaven.

534
00:44:17.622 --> 00:44:21.422
- All right. what's
your idea of heaven?
- Room service.

535
00:44:23.061 --> 00:44:27.725
Oh. he's laughing again.
Well. that's what I want.

536
00:44:27.799 --> 00:44:31.701
I wanna move and go places
and never look back.

537
00:44:31.769 --> 00:44:34.203
Just have fun. forever.

538
00:44:34.272 --> 00:44:38.402
That's my idea of heaven.
Need someone to share it with. though.

539
00:44:38.476 --> 00:44:41.172
You mean Behan.

540
00:44:44.348 --> 00:44:47.215
Well. then...

541
00:44:47.285 --> 00:44:50.015
Why are you with him?

542
00:44:50.088 --> 00:44:54.047
Because he's handsome
and he's charming and...

543
00:44:54.125 --> 00:44:57.959
He's all right.
For now.

544
00:44:58.029 --> 00:45:00.520
Oh. I know. don't say it.
I'm rotten.

545
00:45:00.598 --> 00:45:04.295
I've tried to be good.
It's just so boring.

546
00:45:04.368 --> 00:45:06.836
The way you talk.

547
00:45:06.904 --> 00:45:10.203
Never heard a woman
talk like that?

548
00:45:11.676 --> 00:45:13.974
Never.

549
00:45:14.045 --> 00:45:18.505
I don't have time to be proper.
I wanna live.

550
00:45:18.583 --> 00:45:21.279
I'm a woman.
I like men.

551
00:45:21.352 --> 00:45:25.721
If that means I'm not ladylike.
then I guess I'm just not a lady.

552
00:45:25.790 --> 00:45:29.521
- At least. I'm honest.
- You're different.

553
00:45:29.594 --> 00:45:31.687
There's no arguin' that.

554
00:45:31.762 --> 00:45:35.391
But you're a lady.
all right.

555
00:45:35.466 --> 00:45:38.833
I'll take my oath on it.

556
00:45:43.841 --> 00:45:46.275
- Giddap! Come on!

557
00:46:02.960 --> 00:46:06.657
Is that the opium
Lou gave you?

558
00:46:08.566 --> 00:46:12.093
It's a new bottle.
isn't it?

559
00:46:12.170 --> 00:46:15.105
You better go easy
on that stuff.

560
00:46:15.173 --> 00:46:18.665
Wyatt. leave me alone.

561
00:46:18.743 --> 00:46:22.235
- And where've you been?
- Just out.

562
00:46:22.313 --> 00:46:25.248
- Hmm.
- Ridin'.

563
00:46:29.053 --> 00:46:32.989
- How're you feelin'. Mattie?

564
00:46:35.159 --> 00:46:38.526
Uh. uh...
I don't know. Uh...

565
00:46:38.596 --> 00:46:40.791
I'm all right.

566
00:46:42.066 --> 00:46:44.933
I'm fine.

567
00:46:45.002 --> 00:46:47.994
- You sure?
- Su... I'm sure.

568
00:46:49.407 --> 00:46:53.639
Well. I was
thinkin' today.

569
00:46:53.711 --> 00:46:56.646
we've already made
a pile of money in this place.

570
00:46:56.714 --> 00:46:59.706
If we pulled up stakes
and just moved on. you know.

571
00:46:59.784 --> 00:47:02.810
then we could stay on the move.
keep goin'. see the world.

572
00:47:02.887 --> 00:47:06.618
Just... live on room service
for the rest of our lives.

573
00:47:06.691 --> 00:47:09.159
How'd that be?

574
00:47:09.227 --> 00:47:13.323
Room serv...

575
00:47:13.397 --> 00:47:17.527
Wyatt. what're you
talkin' about?

576
00:47:20.404 --> 00:47:22.599
Nothin'. I just...

577
00:47:22.673 --> 00:47:25.938
Just thinkin' out loud.
and you know I...

578
00:47:27.378 --> 00:47:30.313
Nothin'.

579
00:47:31.749 --> 00:47:34.684
Forget about it.

580
00:47:48.266 --> 00:47:50.700
Ow!

581
00:47:53.304 --> 00:47:56.239
What's she doin' with that lunger?

582
00:48:07.285 --> 00:48:10.311
Hey!

583
00:48:11.822 --> 00:48:14.154
Hey!

584
00:48:14.225 --> 00:48:18.127
Is that 'Old Dog Trey'?
That sounds like 'Old Dog Trey' to me.

585
00:48:19.730 --> 00:48:22.324
Pardon?

586
00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:24.732
You know. Stephen Foster.

587
00:48:24.802 --> 00:48:28.067
'Oh! Susanna.'

588
00:48:28.139 --> 00:48:30.664
'Camptown Races.'

589
00:48:32.543 --> 00:48:34.807
Stephen stinkin' Foster!

590
00:48:34.879 --> 00:48:37.313
Uh. yes. well.

591
00:48:37.381 --> 00:48:40.441
this happens to be
a nocturne.

592
00:48:40.518 --> 00:48:43.385
- A which?
- You know.

593
00:48:43.454 --> 00:48:46.787
- Frederic fucking Chopin.

594
00:48:56.901 --> 00:48:59.335
Oh. yeah.

595
00:49:13.284 --> 00:49:16.219
Boy. I feel great.

596
00:49:18.055 --> 00:49:21.183
I feel... just...

597
00:49:21.258 --> 00:49:24.193
capital.

598
00:49:43.981 --> 00:49:47.815
- Yaahhh!

599
00:49:52.590 --> 00:49:55.855
- Do you see what's
going on in the street?

600
00:49:55.926 --> 00:49:58.793
- Somebody's gotta do something.
- I believe you're the sheriff.

601
00:49:58.863 --> 00:50:03.027
No. no. no. no. This is
not county business. This is
a town matter. Marshal?

602
00:50:03.100 --> 00:50:05.625
Yaahhh!

603
00:50:05.703 --> 00:50:08.729
- Why don't you just leave it alone?

604
00:50:08.806 --> 00:50:13.743
No. I. uh...
I gotta do somethin'.

605
00:50:13.811 --> 00:50:17.474
Wah-hoo-wahhh!

606
00:50:17.548 --> 00:50:20.073
Here's your down card.

607
00:50:39.136 --> 00:50:41.798
- Curly Bill!

608
00:50:44.642 --> 00:50:47.008
Come on now.

609
00:50:47.077 --> 00:50:49.545
Well. howdy. Fred.

610
00:50:49.613 --> 00:50:53.674
Hand those over. Curly.
Hand 'em over.

611
00:50:57.555 --> 00:51:00.080
Why. sure. Dad.

612
00:51:01.759 --> 00:51:04.095
I'm only funnin'.

613
00:51:04.228 --> 00:51:06.253
Here you go.

614
00:51:18.843 --> 00:51:21.676
Fred?

615
00:51:21.745 --> 00:51:24.942
Come on now. Fred?

616
00:51:27.852 --> 00:51:31.219
- Got ol' Fred White!
- Hey. everybody!

617
00:51:31.288 --> 00:51:35.418
Better get him
off the street.

618
00:51:35.493 --> 00:51:38.428
Fred White's dead! They killed him.
They killed Fred White!

619
00:51:38.496 --> 00:51:42.660
- All right. back off.
- Get a rope! String him up!

620
00:51:42.733 --> 00:51:45.566
- Nobody's hangin' anybody.
- He just killed a man!

621
00:51:45.636 --> 00:51:48.799
Then he'll stand trial for it.
Now get back! Move!

622
00:51:50.875 --> 00:51:53.901
Turn him loose!

623
00:52:02.520 --> 00:52:06.115
He said to turn
loose of him.

624
00:52:06.190 --> 00:52:09.956
- Well. I'm not; so. go home.

625
00:52:10.027 --> 00:52:14.964
I swear to God. law dog. you don't
step aside. we'll tear you apart.

626
00:52:15.032 --> 00:52:18.593
All right. you die first.
Get it?

627
00:52:18.669 --> 00:52:23.971
Your friends might get me
in a rush. but not before
I make your head into a canoe.

628
00:52:24.041 --> 00:52:28.501
- He's bluffin'. Let's rush him.
- No... he ain't bluffin'.

629
00:52:28.579 --> 00:52:31.639
You're not as stupid
as you look. Ike.

630
00:52:31.715 --> 00:52:35.446
- Now tell them to get back.
- Go on now. get back.

631
00:52:35.519 --> 00:52:39.216
Go on!
Billy!

632
00:52:39.290 --> 00:52:42.987
He'll kill me.

633
00:52:45.696 --> 00:52:49.393
- And you. music lover.

634
00:52:49.466 --> 00:52:51.696
you're next.

635
00:52:51.769 --> 00:52:55.227
It's the drunk piano player.

636
00:52:55.306 --> 00:52:58.298
You're so drunk.
you can't hit nothin'.

637
00:52:58.375 --> 00:53:01.811
In fact. you're
probably seein' double.

638
00:53:01.879 --> 00:53:06.339
I have two guns.
one for each of ya.

639
00:53:06.417 --> 00:53:09.511
All right. back it up now!

640
00:53:14.892 --> 00:53:17.190
Go home now!

641
00:53:27.938 --> 00:53:31.669
I'll see you soon.

642
00:53:31.742 --> 00:53:35.200
- I'll see you soon.
- We'll meet again.

643
00:53:40.184 --> 00:53:42.880
Well. as you can see.

644
00:53:42.953 --> 00:53:45.751
never a dull moment.

645
00:54:09.980 --> 00:54:13.313
So it takes Judge Spicer
three weeks to get back to town.

646
00:54:13.384 --> 00:54:16.319
and he says. 'Well.
did you actually see it? '

647
00:54:16.387 --> 00:54:19.879
I said. 'No. By the time I got there.
Marshal White had already been shot.'

648
00:54:19.957 --> 00:54:22.892
Then Spicer leans forward
and he says.

649
00:54:22.960 --> 00:54:25.952
- 'Well. can't have a murder
without a witness.'

650
00:54:26.030 --> 00:54:28.658
- What?
- Case dismissed. Can you beat it?

651
00:54:28.732 --> 00:54:32.498
After all that?
Aw. hell. who cares?

652
00:54:32.569 --> 00:54:35.037
None of my business anyway.

653
00:54:35.105 --> 00:54:37.733
Ready to go. Milt?

654
00:54:37.808 --> 00:54:41.369
God. I love this game!
You know. boys. when we're finally set.

655
00:54:41.445 --> 00:54:44.414
we gotta each have
a billiard room in our houses.

656
00:54:44.481 --> 00:54:46.915
I been thinkin'.

657
00:54:46.984 --> 00:54:50.181
maybe we oughta open up
a place of our own. You know?

658
00:54:50.254 --> 00:54:53.690
- There's the real money. Build it up.

659
00:54:53.757 --> 00:54:56.351
Milk it for all it's worth.
then sell it off for a bundle...

660
00:54:56.427 --> 00:55:00.227
and breeze outta this burg
with more money than Cresus
and ready to live like kings.

661
00:55:00.297 --> 00:55:03.789
What d'ya think. Virg?

662
00:55:03.867 --> 00:55:06.961
Virg?

663
00:55:07.037 --> 00:55:09.972
Why don't you and me
take a walk around town...

664
00:55:10.040 --> 00:55:14.204
and see if we can't spot us out
a couple of nice lots?

665
00:55:14.278 --> 00:55:17.441
It's workin' out just
like you said. Wyatt.

666
00:55:17.514 --> 00:55:21.780
- Goddamn. boys. we're lootin'
this burg six ways from Sunday.
- Pretty fun too. isn't it?

667
00:55:21.852 --> 00:55:25.948
- Actually. yeah. I gotta admit.
- Excuse me. Wyatt.
do you have a moment?

668
00:55:26.023 --> 00:55:30.050
- Will you just hear me out?
- Now hold on. Mayor.
He already told you now.

669
00:55:30.127 --> 00:55:32.220
You tell him. Morg.

670
00:55:32.296 --> 00:55:35.823
What about you?
You were a lawman.

671
00:55:37.935 --> 00:55:40.199
- I'm busy.

672
00:55:40.270 --> 00:55:42.397
We're all busy.

673
00:55:42.473 --> 00:55:46.637
Sorry. Mayor. but you're
barkin' up the wrong tree.

674
00:55:46.710 --> 00:55:49.577
You know. you men are makin'
a lot of money in this town.

675
00:55:49.646 --> 00:55:52.376
That's good. That's good.
Good for you.

676
00:55:52.449 --> 00:55:55.680
In the meantime. a lot of
decent people are suffering.

677
00:55:55.753 --> 00:56:00.383
But. please. don't let me take up
any more of your precious time.

678
00:56:04.495 --> 00:56:06.656
Rack 'em.

679
00:56:06.730 --> 00:56:10.188
I tell ya. I'm suffering.
From a hangover.

680
00:56:18.075 --> 00:56:20.339
- Stop that!

681
00:56:20.411 --> 00:56:22.709
Stop. No.

682
00:57:18.035 --> 00:57:21.198
Hold on a minute!
Wait a minute!

683
00:57:21.271 --> 00:57:24.672
- Calm down and listen to me!

684
00:57:24.741 --> 00:57:27.676
Nobody's sayin'
you can't own a gun.

685
00:57:27.744 --> 00:57:30.838
Nobody's even sayin'
you can't carry a gun.

686
00:57:30.914 --> 00:57:34.315
All we're sayin' is you
can't carry a gun in town.

687
00:57:38.222 --> 00:57:42.090
That's not so bad.
is it?

688
00:57:46.597 --> 00:57:49.532
Listen. Mayor. I have
to talk to you about this.

689
00:57:49.600 --> 00:57:52.831
No. we don't have to talk.
You can read. can't you?
It's a town matter.

690
00:57:52.903 --> 00:57:57.704
What in the hell are you doin'?
I told you we weren't gettin' involved.

691
00:57:57.774 --> 00:58:00.368
You got us involved
when you brought us here.

692
00:58:00.444 --> 00:58:03.538
Now you hold on
a minute. Virg.

693
00:58:03.614 --> 00:58:07.209
Hold on nothin'!
I walk around this town and
look these people in the eyes.

694
00:58:07.284 --> 00:58:10.151
It's just like someone's
slappin' me in the face.

695
00:58:10.220 --> 00:58:12.654
These people are afraid
to walk down the street.

696
00:58:12.723 --> 00:58:15.658
and I'm tryin' to make money off
that like some goddamn vulture!

697
00:58:15.726 --> 00:58:19.162
If we're gonna have a future
in this town. it's gotta have
some law and order.

698
00:58:19.229 --> 00:58:21.220
Don't do this to me!

699
00:58:21.298 --> 00:58:24.961
- It's got nothin' to do
with you! It's got to do wi...
- Nothin' to do with me?

700
00:58:25.035 --> 00:58:28.198
I'm your brother. for Christ's sake!
God. I don't believe this!

701
00:58:28.272 --> 00:58:31.730
Talk to him. will you?
Or hit him!

702
00:58:34.645 --> 00:58:36.840
Ah. God. don't tell me!

703
00:58:36.914 --> 00:58:39.348
Like you said. Wyatt.
we're brothers.

704
00:58:39.416 --> 00:58:43.477
Gotta back your brother's play.
Just did like I figured you would.

705
00:58:43.554 --> 00:58:47.354
All right now. you listen
to me. both of ya!

706
00:58:48.792 --> 00:58:51.226
For the first time
in our lives.

707
00:58:51.295 --> 00:58:53.729
we got a chance to stop wandering
and finally be a family.

708
00:58:53.797 --> 00:58:56.766
This is trouble we don't need.
You saw what happened to Fred White.

709
00:58:56.833 --> 00:58:59.063
We know what
we're doin'. Wyatt.

710
00:58:59.136 --> 00:59:03.232
Okay. fine. Say you're right.
say you don't get yourself killed.

711
00:59:03.307 --> 00:59:06.071
There's somethin' else.

712
00:59:06.143 --> 00:59:11.308
All those years I worked those
cow towns. I was only ever mixed
up in one shootin'. just one.

713
00:59:11.381 --> 00:59:14.680
But a man lost his life.
and I took it.

714
00:59:14.751 --> 00:59:17.117
You don't know how
that feels. Morg.

715
00:59:17.187 --> 00:59:20.953
Believe me. boy.
you don't ever wanna know.

716
00:59:21.024 --> 00:59:24.016
Not ever.

717
00:59:30.534 --> 00:59:33.469
Didn't even make a dent. did I?

718
00:59:33.537 --> 00:59:36.870
All right.

719
00:59:36.940 --> 00:59:40.171
You're both makin' a big mistake.

720
00:59:45.983 --> 00:59:52.980
# What remained of our day
in the sunshine #

721
00:59:53.057 --> 00:59:59.189
- # That brightened
our pathway a while #
- Do you wanna ante?

722
00:59:59.263 --> 01:00:06.032
- Yeah. fine.
- # Come and sit by my side
if you love me #

723
01:00:06.103 --> 01:00:13.066
# Do not hasten
to bid me adieu #

724
01:00:13.144 --> 01:00:20.209
# But remember
the Red River Valley #

725
01:00:20.284 --> 01:00:25.688
# And the girl who has
loved you so true #

726
01:00:25.756 --> 01:00:30.591
- What do you think of the singer?
- # Will you think of the vow... #

727
01:00:30.661 --> 01:00:33.721
Nice voice.

728
01:00:33.798 --> 01:00:37.859
Wyatt. Doc won't quit.
He's been at it for 36 hours straight.

729
01:00:37.935 --> 01:00:40.870
Clanton and the McLaury brothers
came in an hour ago.

730
01:00:40.938 --> 01:00:46.535
- I tried to get him to go to bed.
but he won't let go.
- I know. and nobody can make him.

731
01:00:49.480 --> 01:00:54.315
Wyatt. just in time.
Pull up a chair.

732
01:00:54.385 --> 01:00:58.253
Doc. you been hittin' it
awful hard. haven't ya?

733
01:00:58.322 --> 01:01:03.692
Nonsense. I've not yet
begun to defile myself.

734
01:01:03.761 --> 01:01:06.252
I was wonderin' if you
wouldn't wanna go on over
to the Crystal Palace...

735
01:01:06.330 --> 01:01:08.924
I will not be pawed at.
thank you very much.

736
01:01:08.999 --> 01:01:10.933
- I'm sorry.
- That's right.

737
01:01:11.001 --> 01:01:13.970
Doc can go on day and night.
and then some.

738
01:01:15.773 --> 01:01:20.210
That's my loving man.
Have another one. my loving man.

739
01:01:20.277 --> 01:01:23.212
I'm in.

740
01:01:24.281 --> 01:01:26.215
Straight.

741
01:01:26.283 --> 01:01:30.049
Loving man.
you been called.

742
01:01:37.194 --> 01:01:39.355
Oops.

743
01:01:42.700 --> 01:01:44.930
What is that now?

744
01:01:45.002 --> 01:01:50.133
That 12 hands in a row. Holliday?
Son-of-a-bitch. nobody's that lucky.

745
01:01:51.208 --> 01:01:55.008
Why. Ike.
whatever do you mean?

746
01:01:55.079 --> 01:01:57.809
Take it easy. boys.

747
01:01:59.216 --> 01:02:02.879
Maybe poker's
just not your game. Ike.

748
01:02:04.288 --> 01:02:08.622
I know. let's have
a spelling contest.

749
01:02:08.692 --> 01:02:12.287
- How 'bout if I just
wring your scrawny neck?
- Enough. Ike.

750
01:02:13.631 --> 01:02:16.259
Are you takin'
his part? Huh?

751
01:02:16.333 --> 01:02:19.496
I'm the one
who got cheated!

752
01:02:19.570 --> 01:02:24.303
You goddamn pimps!
You all in it together.

753
01:02:24.375 --> 01:02:27.776
Nobody's in anything.
Ike. you're drunk.
Go on home and sleep it off.

754
01:02:27.845 --> 01:02:30.609
Get your goddamn hands off me!

755
01:02:30.681 --> 01:02:33.206
Don't you ever put
your hands on me. see?

756
01:02:33.284 --> 01:02:36.947
Don't you ever try to manhandle
a Cowboy. 'cause we'll cut
your goddamn pimp's heart out.

757
01:02:37.021 --> 01:02:40.149
- Understand me. pimp?
- Don't you threaten me.
you little son-of-a-bitch!

758
01:02:40.224 --> 01:02:42.784
All right! All right!
Come on. easy. Virg. easy!

759
01:02:42.860 --> 01:02:45.829
You just go on home and
forget about it. huh. Ike?

760
01:02:45.896 --> 01:02:48.364
Come on. Virg.

761
01:02:48.432 --> 01:02:50.866
I ain't gonna forget nothin'.

762
01:02:50.935 --> 01:02:55.565
Well. that certainly was a bust.

763
01:02:55.639 --> 01:03:00.906
Come. darlin'. Let's seek
our entertainment elsewhere.

764
01:03:00.978 --> 01:03:04.141
Forget it. Virg. Go on.
Get some fresh air.

765
01:03:15.593 --> 01:03:17.527
What's wrong. Doc?

766
01:03:17.595 --> 01:03:19.859
Nothin'. Not a thing.

767
01:03:19.930 --> 01:03:22.558
I'm right as the mail.

768
01:03:25.736 --> 01:03:28.000
Doc? Doc!

769
01:03:28.072 --> 01:03:31.269
All right. get him up.
Let's get him to the hotel.

770
01:03:40.317 --> 01:03:42.877
- What's wrong with him?
- Lunger.

771
01:03:42.953 --> 01:03:45.751
Yeah. well. I hope you die.

772
01:03:46.824 --> 01:03:49.349
Give me my guns.

773
01:03:51.395 --> 01:03:53.329
My rifle.

774
01:03:53.397 --> 01:03:56.525
Goddamn bastards.
Think they can cheat me.

775
01:03:56.600 --> 01:03:58.659
Nobody cheated you. Ike.
Just go home.

776
01:04:00.170 --> 01:04:03.571
I don't take no mouth
from no bartenders. neither.

777
01:04:03.641 --> 01:04:05.575
There. ya see?

778
01:04:05.643 --> 01:04:09.101
Give somebody a rap on the beezer.
get some respect around here.

779
01:04:09.179 --> 01:04:13.548
You tell the Earps. I see 'em
on the street and Doc Holliday.

780
01:04:13.617 --> 01:04:17.314
I'm gonna send them to hell
on a shutter. You tell 'em that...

781
01:04:23.327 --> 01:04:25.761
Pick these guns up.

782
01:04:25.829 --> 01:04:27.763
Come on.

783
01:04:42.579 --> 01:04:45.104
Come on. Ike.

784
01:04:45.182 --> 01:04:47.173
Come on!

785
01:04:49.286 --> 01:04:52.119
- Hey. you walkin'?
- Leave me alone.

786
01:04:58.629 --> 01:05:01.427
- You gonna give Ike back his guns.
- Not 'til he sobers up.

787
01:05:01.498 --> 01:05:05.264
Wearin' that badge
don't make you right.

788
01:05:05.335 --> 01:05:07.929
Who the hell
you think you are?

789
01:05:11.175 --> 01:05:15.635
- Watch the way you walk.
you stupid bastard.
- Easy. kid. I'm sorry.

790
01:05:15.713 --> 01:05:18.341
I ain't easy
and I ain't your kid.

791
01:05:18.415 --> 01:05:21.782
You take your sorry
and shove it up your ass.

792
01:05:24.888 --> 01:05:27.015
I'll fight you right now.

793
01:05:33.564 --> 01:05:35.498
Goddammit!

794
01:05:35.566 --> 01:05:37.534
You're gonna bleed.

795
01:05:37.601 --> 01:05:41.037
You got a fight comin'.
Comin' today.

796
01:05:45.042 --> 01:05:47.977
Bastards! We're comin'!

797
01:05:55.085 --> 01:05:57.610
Your condition's
quite advanced.

798
01:05:57.688 --> 01:06:01.852
I'd say you lost some 60%
of your lung tissue. maybe more.

799
01:06:01.925 --> 01:06:03.859
What's the verdict?

800
01:06:03.927 --> 01:06:08.830
Two years. Two days.
Hard to say. if you stop now:

801
01:06:08.899 --> 01:06:11.800
Your smokin'.
your drinkin'.

802
01:06:11.869 --> 01:06:14.133
your gamblin'.
your night life.

803
01:06:14.204 --> 01:06:17.002
You need complete rest.

804
01:06:18.408 --> 01:06:22.640
What I mean is.
you must attempt to. uh. deny...

805
01:06:22.713 --> 01:06:27.207
- your. uh. marital impulse.
- Get out of my sight.

806
01:06:45.602 --> 01:06:48.503
- How are you feeling. Doc?
- Mmm. better.

807
01:06:48.572 --> 01:06:50.938
That's good.

808
01:06:51.008 --> 01:06:53.841
I knew it wasn't nothing.

809
01:06:55.145 --> 01:06:57.670
We must talk. darlin'.

810
01:06:59.082 --> 01:07:01.414
It appears. uh...

811
01:07:01.485 --> 01:07:06.787
we must redefine the nature
of our association.

812
01:07:11.261 --> 01:07:14.697
I'm a good woman
to you. Doc.

813
01:07:14.765 --> 01:07:17.325
Don't I always
take care of ya?

814
01:07:17.401 --> 01:07:20.302
Nobody cares for you
like me.

815
01:07:21.405 --> 01:07:23.600
I'm a good woman.

816
01:07:25.142 --> 01:07:29.101
Yes. it's true.
you are a good woman.

817
01:07:41.658 --> 01:07:44.024
Then again...

818
01:07:44.094 --> 01:07:48.698
you may be the Antichrist.

819
01:08:09.385 --> 01:08:12.013
Goddamn.

820
01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:16.616
Now there's six of 'em.
Hell. this is like a bad dream.

821
01:08:16.692 --> 01:08:19.991
Just stay calm. Use your head.
It'll be all right.

822
01:08:23.299 --> 01:08:25.460
Just the same. though...

823
01:08:26.836 --> 01:08:29.805
Guess maybe you better
swear me in.

824
01:09:04.807 --> 01:09:09.210
Those Cowboys been telling everybody
in town they're gonna clean you out.

825
01:09:09.278 --> 01:09:12.736
They're back there in that lot
behind the O.K. Corral.

826
01:09:14.116 --> 01:09:16.641
- Thank you. Mayor.
- What're you doin' out of bed. Doc?

827
01:09:16.719 --> 01:09:19.119
What in the hell's goin' on?
Five people come up to my room...

828
01:09:19.188 --> 01:09:23.215
tellin' me the Clantons and McLaurys
are gunnin' for us.

829
01:09:23.292 --> 01:09:27.854
- We goin' down there or not?
What are we gonna do?
- Wait 'til the liquor wears off.

830
01:09:27.930 --> 01:09:30.455
Soon as they start gettin' headaches.
they'll lose interest.

831
01:09:30.533 --> 01:09:33.730
Lose interest. hell.
They're threatenin' our lives.

832
01:09:33.803 --> 01:09:37.102
- You'll never make that stick.
- They're carryin' guns. Wyatt.

833
01:09:37.173 --> 01:09:39.107
Christ's sake. Virg.
that's a misdemeanor.

834
01:09:39.175 --> 01:09:42.872
You go arrest them. something
goes wrong. maybe somebody
really gets his head broken.

835
01:09:42.945 --> 01:09:46.403
You'll have Cowboys
comin' around lookin' for
trouble from here to Christmas.

836
01:09:46.482 --> 01:09:49.918
- You want to risk all that
over a misdemeanor?
- Damn right I'll risk it.

837
01:09:49.985 --> 01:09:52.385
They're breakin' the law.

838
01:09:58.127 --> 01:10:01.528
It's not your problem. Doc.
You don't have to mix up in this.

839
01:10:03.732 --> 01:10:07.532
That is a hell of a thing
for you to say to me.

840
01:10:17.680 --> 01:10:20.513
All right. Virg.

841
01:10:22.618 --> 01:10:25.985
Your call.
Give Doc the shotgun.

842
01:10:27.223 --> 01:10:29.350
They'll be less apt
to get nerv-i-ous...

843
01:10:29.425 --> 01:10:31.655
if he's on
the street howitzer.

844
01:11:15.404 --> 01:11:17.338
Hey! Bang bang
bang bang bang!

845
01:11:17.406 --> 01:11:20.034
Go on! Get home!

846
01:11:21.110 --> 01:11:23.635
Goddamn kid.

847
01:11:34.056 --> 01:11:37.685
How the hell did we
get ourselves into this?

848
01:11:40.629 --> 01:11:43.792
You don't have to worry about a thing.
I just disarmed them.

849
01:11:43.866 --> 01:11:46.460
You did?
Come on. boys.

850
01:11:46.535 --> 01:11:49.834
Gentlemen. I'm not
gonna allow any trouble.

851
01:12:13.162 --> 01:12:16.654
We're here to disarm you.
Throw up your hands.

852
01:12:20.369 --> 01:12:23.167
Hold it!
That's not what I want!

853
01:12:57.473 --> 01:12:59.407
Oh. my God.

854
01:13:08.183 --> 01:13:10.947
Billy! Billy!

855
01:13:17.559 --> 01:13:20.027
Stop! No! No!

856
01:13:20.095 --> 01:13:22.825
Don't shoot!
I got no gun!

857
01:13:22.898 --> 01:13:26.197
- Please don't shoot me!
I got no gun!
- This fight's commenced!

858
01:13:26.268 --> 01:13:28.532
Get to fightin' or get away!

859
01:13:30.005 --> 01:13:32.997
- Unh!
- Shut the door!

860
01:13:37.379 --> 01:13:39.847
Aah!

861
01:13:48.357 --> 01:13:50.757
Give me your goddamned gun!
Damn it!

862
01:13:50.826 --> 01:13:53.294
Billy! Billy!

863
01:13:53.362 --> 01:13:55.694
Doc. behind us!

864
01:14:22.224 --> 01:14:24.749
I got you now.
you son-of-a-bitch.

865
01:14:24.827 --> 01:14:26.761
You're a daisy if you do.

866
01:14:40.943 --> 01:14:43.468
Morgan. hold quiet now.

867
01:14:54.356 --> 01:14:56.950
Here you go.
Easy. Easy. man.

868
01:14:57.025 --> 01:14:59.823
- I got you. All right.
- All right!

869
01:15:01.797 --> 01:15:04.357
All of you
are under arrest.

870
01:15:15.010 --> 01:15:18.912
I don't think I'll let you
arrest us today. Behan.

871
01:15:47.676 --> 01:15:49.610
Virg!

872
01:15:49.678 --> 01:15:52.238
- Virgil!

873
01:16:11.900 --> 01:16:15.336
Well. I guess we did
our good deed for today. Mayor.

874
01:17:40.022 --> 01:17:43.583
You were right.
It's nothin' like I thought.

875
01:17:43.659 --> 01:17:47.151
- I almost wish that...
- I know. Morgan.

876
01:17:48.864 --> 01:17:50.957
I know. Me too.

877
01:18:03.278 --> 01:18:05.405
Outta the way!
Yee-haw!

878
01:18:09.551 --> 01:18:11.519
Gettin' warmer.

879
01:18:11.587 --> 01:18:14.147
Guess spring's comin'.

880
01:18:14.223 --> 01:18:19.024
- Hello. Billy. I say hello.
- It's deputy! And I don't
want to talk to you!

881
01:18:19.094 --> 01:18:21.358
Those men you killed
were my friends.

882
01:18:21.430 --> 01:18:25.526
I'm just a nothin'. But if
I wasn't. I'd fight you right now.

883
01:18:25.601 --> 01:18:28.001
so I don't
want to talk to you.

884
01:18:30.205 --> 01:18:32.537
All they ever did
was laugh at him.

885
01:18:41.050 --> 01:18:44.781
Sister boy should've
stuck around.

886
01:18:46.555 --> 01:18:50.992
- What do you want. Ringo?
- I want your blood.

887
01:18:52.561 --> 01:18:54.961
And I want your souls.

888
01:18:55.030 --> 01:18:57.726
And I want 'em both right now.

889
01:18:57.800 --> 01:19:01.167
- I don't want any more trouble.
- Well. ya got trouble!

890
01:19:02.805 --> 01:19:05.899
And it starts with you.

891
01:19:09.478 --> 01:19:12.038
I'm not gonna
fight you. Ringo.

892
01:19:13.348 --> 01:19:15.509
There's no money in it.

893
01:19:15.584 --> 01:19:17.882
Sober up.
Come on. boys.

894
01:19:17.953 --> 01:19:20.387
You wretched slugs.

895
01:19:20.456 --> 01:19:23.857
Don't any of ya have the guts
to play for blood?

896
01:19:23.926 --> 01:19:26.417
I'm your huckleberry.

897
01:19:26.495 --> 01:19:29.896
That's just my game.

898
01:19:37.039 --> 01:19:42.033
All right. lunger.
You go to hell.

899
01:19:42.111 --> 01:19:46.445
- I'll put you out of your misery.
- Say when.

900
01:19:46.515 --> 01:19:50.144
- Johnny. don't!
- No. Johnny! Whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa!

901
01:19:50.219 --> 01:19:52.244
- Get off!
- Easy now! It ain't nothin'.

902
01:19:52.321 --> 01:19:54.949
- Get off!
- Don't mind him!

903
01:19:55.023 --> 01:19:58.049
He's just drunk.
that's all.

904
01:19:58.127 --> 01:20:01.255
Cool down. Johnny!

905
01:20:01.330 --> 01:20:03.924
No! No!

906
01:20:03.999 --> 01:20:06.797
I want them spittin' blood!

907
01:20:06.869 --> 01:20:10.168
- Easy. son. easy!
Now ain't the time!
- Slow down. Ringo.

908
01:20:13.142 --> 01:20:16.805
I tell ya. boys. even I'm wary
of what's gonna happen
once Ringo runs this outfit.

909
01:20:16.879 --> 01:20:19.575
God have mercy!

910
01:20:19.648 --> 01:20:23.607
Juanito. their time will come.
- Gentlemen.

911
01:20:23.685 --> 01:20:26.620
- You can pull it. boy!
- Let's go get sauced!

912
01:20:26.688 --> 01:20:28.883
- Barber.
- Yes. sir?

913
01:20:31.193 --> 01:20:33.127
Proceed. sir.

914
01:20:49.077 --> 01:20:53.480
Listen to me.
I need to speak with you.

915
01:20:53.549 --> 01:20:56.074
Not now. I'm busy.

916
01:20:56.151 --> 01:20:58.949
I see what's going on
between you and Wyatt.

917
01:20:59.021 --> 01:21:02.752
I'm not a fool.
And listen to me.

918
01:21:02.825 --> 01:21:07.524
Lots of so-called hard cases and
tough nuts come and go around this town.

919
01:21:07.596 --> 01:21:12.033
but none of them has a clue
about the real play... none of them.

920
01:21:12.100 --> 01:21:15.695
Now after tonight. there'll be one man
in charge of Tombstone.

921
01:21:15.771 --> 01:21:19.867
You'll be happy to know him.
Bet on it.

922
01:21:28.083 --> 01:21:30.881
Gonna be one of those nights.

923
01:21:33.589 --> 01:21:36.820
It's gettin' late. boys.
I'm gonna go to bed.

924
01:21:36.892 --> 01:21:39.827
- Good night. Virg.
- Good night. Morg.

925
01:21:39.895 --> 01:21:43.661
Bundle up. Virg.
It's gettin' cold out there.

926
01:21:43.732 --> 01:21:45.597
Yeah.

927
01:22:12.394 --> 01:22:15.261
Tower of Babel.

928
01:22:15.330 --> 01:22:17.821
Death and the Devil.

929
01:22:17.900 --> 01:22:22.394
- Oh. dear.
- Oh. Allie. I wish you'd learn
to play a real card game.

930
01:22:27.009 --> 01:22:29.773
- More tea. Mattie?
- Mm-mmm. No. no.

931
01:22:29.845 --> 01:22:31.779
- Are you all right. Mattie?
- Yes.

932
01:22:31.847 --> 01:22:34.475
- Are you expecting someone?
- Only Virg.

933
01:22:39.755 --> 01:22:43.122
Please. I know it's awful
to come here. but listen.

934
01:22:43.191 --> 01:22:45.819
I think something's
gonna happen tonight.

935
01:22:47.930 --> 01:22:50.421
It's Virg.

936
01:22:50.499 --> 01:22:53.127
- No! Get down!

937
01:23:11.086 --> 01:23:13.418
That thunder's
sure gettin' close.

938
01:23:25.300 --> 01:23:28.565
Virgil. What'd ya forget?

939
01:23:39.614 --> 01:23:42.082
Wyatt.

940
01:23:54.162 --> 01:23:57.256
Will you hurry
with that water. please?

941
01:23:57.332 --> 01:23:59.493
Come on. Lou.

942
01:24:02.037 --> 01:24:04.597
Wyatt! Wyatt!

943
01:24:06.842 --> 01:24:09.640
They hit Claude's house too.
shot up his wife.

944
01:24:09.711 --> 01:24:11.872
His wife!
Whoever heard of that?

945
01:24:11.947 --> 01:24:15.178
They're bugs. Wyatt. All that
smart talk about live and let live.

946
01:24:15.250 --> 01:24:17.184
There ain't no live
and let live with bugs.

947
01:24:17.252 --> 01:24:19.584
All right. you listen to me now.
We gotta get out of here.

948
01:24:19.654 --> 01:24:22.714
Get out of here?
Listen to yourself. Wyatt.

949
01:24:22.791 --> 01:24:25.624
Lie down and crawl or you might
get hurt? What kind of talk is that?

950
01:24:25.694 --> 01:24:27.685
- Do you see what's happening here?
- What?

951
01:24:27.763 --> 01:24:31.028
What do you mean?
What are you saying?

952
01:24:31.099 --> 01:24:33.033
No. Please. no.

953
01:24:33.101 --> 01:24:36.400
I'm afraid your husband's
going to lose the use of his arm.

954
01:24:36.471 --> 01:24:39.031
Oh. God. no.

955
01:24:39.107 --> 01:24:42.167
Don't worry. Allie girl.

956
01:24:42.244 --> 01:24:45.577
I still got one good arm
to hold you with.

957
01:24:47.215 --> 01:24:49.342
Goddamn...

958
01:24:49.417 --> 01:24:53.979
- Goddamn sons-of-bitches!
- Morgan. wait a minute! Virg...

959
01:24:54.055 --> 01:24:56.421
- You had to be so damned smart.
- I'm sorry. Allie.

960
01:24:56.491 --> 01:24:58.755
I told you. Virg.

961
01:24:58.827 --> 01:25:01.125
- Not now. Wyatt.
- All right.

962
01:25:01.196 --> 01:25:03.357
- All right. what do you want me to do?

963
01:25:03.431 --> 01:25:07.424
- Just leave me alone. for God's sakes.
- Virg...

964
01:25:07.502 --> 01:25:10.471
He doesn't want
to talk now. Wyatt!

965
01:25:26.554 --> 01:25:30.285
I heard about what they did
to your women. That was wrong.

966
01:25:30.358 --> 01:25:34.556
I'm here to let you know that it
wasn't me. I had no part of it.

967
01:25:34.629 --> 01:25:38.963
No? Brothers to the bone.
right. McMasters?

968
01:25:39.033 --> 01:25:43.265
No. Not anymore.
Not after this night.

969
01:25:43.338 --> 01:25:47.741
He's right. Wyatt. You want us
for anything. we're with you.

970
01:25:47.809 --> 01:25:49.777
Come on.

971
01:26:52.140 --> 01:26:55.075
Hold him!

972
01:26:55.143 --> 01:26:59.079
- No! Get her out of here! Jesus!

973
01:26:59.147 --> 01:27:03.379
- Somebody shut that dog up!

974
01:27:06.120 --> 01:27:08.714
- I said hold him. goddammit!

975
01:27:08.790 --> 01:27:11.418
- Somebody get that
goddamn dog out of here!

976
01:27:11.492 --> 01:27:14.950
The bullet's too deep.
I can't get it out.

977
01:27:17.198 --> 01:27:19.826
- The way it's lodged
in there... I'm sorry.

978
01:27:19.901 --> 01:27:22.995
Easy. Morg.
Is that better?

979
01:27:24.072 --> 01:27:26.006
Yeah.

980
01:27:28.576 --> 01:27:32.774
You were right. Wyatt.
They got me good.

981
01:27:34.616 --> 01:27:38.882
Don't let 'em get you. brother.
You're the one.

982
01:27:39.954 --> 01:27:42.787
Easy. Morg.

983
01:27:42.857 --> 01:27:45.917
Don't worry about that. now.

984
01:27:49.797 --> 01:27:53.130
Remember what I said
about seein' a light when you're dyin'?

985
01:27:53.201 --> 01:27:56.659
Yeah. Yeah.

986
01:27:56.738 --> 01:27:58.899
That ain't true.

987
01:27:58.973 --> 01:28:01.908
I can't see a damn thing.

988
01:28:04.946 --> 01:28:06.880
Morg?

989
01:28:11.252 --> 01:28:13.186
Morg!

990
01:28:18.860 --> 01:28:20.794
Morg?

991
01:28:34.842 --> 01:28:36.776
No.

992
01:28:38.780 --> 01:28:41.214
Morgan! No!

993
01:28:41.282 --> 01:28:44.979
Morgan. don't die!
I love you!

994
01:28:45.053 --> 01:28:47.112
Don't die!

995
01:28:59.867 --> 01:29:02.961
Why? Why him?

996
01:29:06.307 --> 01:29:10.573
- No. No. get away from me!
- Wyatt!

997
01:29:11.746 --> 01:29:14.840
Can't you see?
Get away from me!

998
01:29:49.851 --> 01:29:52.649
Morgan!

999
01:30:43.738 --> 01:30:46.730
And so she walked
out of our lives forever.

1000
01:31:05.092 --> 01:31:07.026
Giddup!

1001
01:31:21.342 --> 01:31:24.834
Want you to know it's over.

1002
01:31:27.215 --> 01:31:29.308
Well.

1003
01:31:29.383 --> 01:31:31.351
Bye.

1004
01:31:33.354 --> 01:31:36.016
You smell that. Bill?

1005
01:31:37.625 --> 01:31:39.786
Smells like someone died.

1006
01:31:41.362 --> 01:31:45.059
Jesus. Johnny.

1007
01:31:55.042 --> 01:31:57.943
- Giddyap!

1008
01:31:58.012 --> 01:32:00.947
Adios. cabrones.

1009
01:32:07.221 --> 01:32:09.155
Ike.

1010
01:32:10.291 --> 01:32:13.692
Take Stillwell and finish it.

1011
01:32:29.176 --> 01:32:32.634
Now. you take care of yourself...

1012
01:32:32.713 --> 01:32:36.376
- That's Virgil with the women.
- He's mine!

1013
01:32:36.450 --> 01:32:39.817
- All aboard!
- Hey. Mattie! Where's Wyatt?

1014
01:32:39.887 --> 01:32:42.515
Right behind you. Stillwell.

1015
01:32:42.590 --> 01:32:44.751
- Aah!
- No!

1016
01:32:59.640 --> 01:33:01.574
Sweet Jesus.

1017
01:33:19.760 --> 01:33:21.785
All right. Clanton.

1018
01:33:21.862 --> 01:33:25.992
You called down the thunder.
Well. now you got it.

1019
01:33:27.968 --> 01:33:31.904
You see that? It says.
'United States Marshal.'

1020
01:33:31.972 --> 01:33:34.497
Wyatt.
Please don't kill me. Please.

1021
01:33:34.575 --> 01:33:38.875
Take a good look at him. Ike.
'cause that's how you're gonna end up.

1022
01:33:41.014 --> 01:33:43.574
The Cowboys are finished.
You understand me?

1023
01:33:43.650 --> 01:33:47.177
I see a red sash.
I kill the man wearin' it.

1024
01:33:47.254 --> 01:33:49.279
So run. you cur.

1025
01:33:50.557 --> 01:33:55.221
Run! Tell all the other curs
the law is comin'!

1026
01:33:55.295 --> 01:33:57.627
You tell 'em I'm comin'!

1027
01:33:57.698 --> 01:34:00.633
And hell's comin'
with me. you hear?

1028
01:34:00.701 --> 01:34:03.499
Hell's comin' with me!

1029
01:34:36.637 --> 01:34:38.571
Nobody move!

1030
01:34:38.639 --> 01:34:42.097
- Nonsense. By all means. move.
-

1031
01:35:56.016 --> 01:35:58.780
-
- Get down!

1032
01:36:09.896 --> 01:36:13.024
Hey. Wyatt!

1033
01:36:13.100 --> 01:36:15.261
How the hell are ya?

1034
01:36:21.708 --> 01:36:24.370
Ohh!

1035
01:36:27.614 --> 01:36:29.878
I got some boys
over there behind ya!

1036
01:36:29.950 --> 01:36:32.919
Got you in a little crossfire.
How do ya like that?

1037
01:36:35.789 --> 01:36:38.758
Come on! Think of
something fast. would ya?

1038
01:36:40.961 --> 01:36:45.227
Wyatt?
Hey. Wyatt.

1039
01:36:45.299 --> 01:36:47.267
- No.
- Wyatt!

1040
01:36:49.236 --> 01:36:51.363
- No.
- Wyatt. what are you doin'?

1041
01:36:51.438 --> 01:36:53.770
Look at that.

1042
01:36:53.840 --> 01:36:56.809
Yeah.

1043
01:36:56.877 --> 01:36:59.243
Come and get some. boy.

1044
01:37:04.184 --> 01:37:06.243
No! Let me!

1045
01:37:12.059 --> 01:37:15.222
- No.

1046
01:37:15.295 --> 01:37:19.061
- Son-of-a-bitch.
- No!

1047
01:37:24.104 --> 01:37:26.072
Jesus Christ!

1048
01:37:30.344 --> 01:37:32.835
Yaahh!

1049
01:37:36.116 --> 01:37:38.778
No. No!

1050
01:37:50.630 --> 01:37:53.656
Did you ever see anything
like that before?

1051
01:37:53.734 --> 01:37:57.295
- Hell. I ain't never even
heard of anything like that.
- Nothin'.

1052
01:37:58.372 --> 01:38:00.306
Where is he?

1053
01:38:00.374 --> 01:38:03.810
Down by the creek.

1054
01:38:03.910 --> 01:38:06.208
walkin' on water.

1055
01:38:06.279 --> 01:38:09.544
Well. let's hope he's got
another miracle up his sleeve.

1056
01:38:09.616 --> 01:38:13.609
'Cause if I know Ringo.
he's headed straight for us.

1057
01:38:13.687 --> 01:38:18.021
Well. if they were my brothers.
I'd want revenge too.

1058
01:38:18.091 --> 01:38:20.821
No. Make no mistake.

1059
01:38:20.894 --> 01:38:24.193
It's not revenge he's after.

1060
01:38:26.066 --> 01:38:28.296
It's a reckoning.

1061
01:38:38.512 --> 01:38:43.142
Doc. You ought to be in bed. What
the hell you doin' this for anyway?

1062
01:38:43.216 --> 01:38:45.707
Wyatt Earp is my friend.

1063
01:38:45.786 --> 01:38:48.949
Hell. I got lots of friends.

1064
01:38:50.957 --> 01:38:53.050
I don't.

1065
01:39:03.403 --> 01:39:06.566
Whoa! Whoa!

1066
01:39:11.611 --> 01:39:13.545
My God.

1067
01:39:16.683 --> 01:39:19.584
- Are you all right?
- What do you care?

1068
01:39:19.653 --> 01:39:22.019
It was your friends
that did it.

1069
01:39:24.224 --> 01:39:27.887
Must've been Claiborne and Fuller.
They left here last night.

1070
01:39:27.961 --> 01:39:30.759
Aw. no.

1071
01:39:30.831 --> 01:39:33.664
They tried to take my watch.

1072
01:39:33.733 --> 01:39:37.635
He cursed them for cowards.
and they shot him.

1073
01:39:38.705 --> 01:39:42.505
I don't understand
any of this.

1074
01:39:42.576 --> 01:39:45.044
I just know it's ugly.

1075
01:39:45.111 --> 01:39:47.705
You're all ugly.

1076
01:39:47.781 --> 01:39:51.376
and he was beautiful.

1077
01:39:51.451 --> 01:39:55.751
He tried to bring something
fine into your ugly world.
and you shot him for it.

1078
01:39:59.960 --> 01:40:01.985
Not that you care.

1079
01:40:13.640 --> 01:40:16.837
- Billy. Where you goin'?
- I'm not goin' with you.

1080
01:40:16.910 --> 01:40:19.208
Billy!
Billy. get back here!

1081
01:40:19.279 --> 01:40:21.839
I'm sorry. sir.
but we got to have some law.

1082
01:40:21.915 --> 01:40:25.749
- Billy!
- Let him go. Who cares?

1083
01:40:25.819 --> 01:40:29.152
Yaahh! Get the hell
outta here! Go on!

1084
01:40:29.222 --> 01:40:32.055
Party's over. boys.
Let's go!

1085
01:40:46.940 --> 01:40:48.874
Whoa.

1086
01:40:54.379 --> 01:40:57.542
Ringo and Behan
are out front.

1087
01:40:57.616 --> 01:41:01.643
There is about 30 of 'em.

1088
01:41:02.787 --> 01:41:04.721
They're all wearin' badges.

1089
01:41:06.658 --> 01:41:08.853
Christ.

1090
01:41:08.927 --> 01:41:13.057
We gotta find
a place to hole up.

1091
01:41:13.131 --> 01:41:15.258
Doc.

1092
01:41:15.333 --> 01:41:17.267
Grab him.

1093
01:41:19.537 --> 01:41:21.471
I got him.

1094
01:41:22.107 --> 01:41:24.041
I got him!

1095
01:41:29.648 --> 01:41:31.582
Is this Henry Hooker's ranch?

1096
01:41:31.650 --> 01:41:34.312
That's right.
And I'm Hooker.

1097
01:41:34.386 --> 01:41:36.684
We got a sick man.

1098
01:41:36.755 --> 01:41:38.746
And our horses are done in.

1099
01:41:38.823 --> 01:41:41.189
Put him up at my place.

1100
01:41:41.259 --> 01:41:43.386
as long as it's just tonight.

1101
01:41:43.461 --> 01:41:45.429
We're in debt to ya.

1102
01:41:52.704 --> 01:41:58.199
I know you boys have got to keep movin'.
but he looks pretty bad to me.

1103
01:42:01.546 --> 01:42:05.505
- Whoa!
- I. uh...

1104
01:42:26.071 --> 01:42:29.336
They got held up.
and their boss actor got killed.

1105
01:42:29.407 --> 01:42:32.706
They came here to water the horses.
then they'll push on.

1106
01:42:49.994 --> 01:42:53.930
I'm sorry about your friend.
And I'm... I'm sorry that I...

1107
01:42:53.998 --> 01:42:57.229
I forgave you
the moment you said it.

1108
01:42:57.302 --> 01:43:00.032
You did? Well...

1109
01:43:01.272 --> 01:43:03.206
Thank you.

1110
01:43:04.542 --> 01:43:06.601
All set.

1111
01:43:08.646 --> 01:43:10.944
I have to go.

1112
01:43:13.585 --> 01:43:15.553
Wait.

1113
01:43:35.273 --> 01:43:37.241
- Hyah!

1114
01:43:37.308 --> 01:43:39.503
Giddup!

1115
01:44:01.533 --> 01:44:03.967
What the hell is that?

1116
01:44:23.721 --> 01:44:26.656
They got McMasters!

1117
01:44:26.724 --> 01:44:29.056
Geez!

1118
01:44:29.127 --> 01:44:31.721
Ringo wanted to make sure
he got your attention. Marshal!

1119
01:44:31.796 --> 01:44:34.788
He wants a straight-up fight.
just you and him.

1120
01:44:34.866 --> 01:44:37.130
to settle this thing
once and for all.

1121
01:44:37.202 --> 01:44:40.831
Oak grove at the mouth
of Silver Springs canyon. 7:00!

1122
01:44:40.905 --> 01:44:43.840
You tell him I'll be there!

1123
01:44:43.908 --> 01:44:47.503
- Are you crazy?
- I'll be there!

1124
01:44:47.579 --> 01:44:50.070
It's not finished.

1125
01:45:05.029 --> 01:45:08.123
After I'm done
with Wyatt Earp.

1126
01:45:08.199 --> 01:45:13.136
take your Cowboys and finish off
Creek Johnson and Texas Jack.

1127
01:45:14.572 --> 01:45:16.563
You burn 'em. Ike.

1128
01:45:18.743 --> 01:45:23.407
- Burn 'em all.
- Hell. Johnny.
he ain't even gonna show.

1129
01:45:23.481 --> 01:45:25.608
Giddap!

1130
01:45:25.683 --> 01:45:28.345
He'll show.

1131
01:45:30.922 --> 01:45:35.188
I spent my whole life not knowin'
what I wanted outta life.

1132
01:45:35.260 --> 01:45:37.751
just chasin' my tail.

1133
01:45:37.829 --> 01:45:41.526
Now for the first time
I know exactly what I want.

1134
01:45:41.599 --> 01:45:43.999
and who.

1135
01:45:45.103 --> 01:45:47.970
And that's
the damnable misery of it.

1136
01:45:52.911 --> 01:45:55.573
What makes a man
like Ringo. Doc?

1137
01:45:55.647 --> 01:45:58.639
What makes him
do the things he does?

1138
01:45:58.716 --> 01:46:01.480
A man like Ringo...

1139
01:46:01.553 --> 01:46:05.785
got a great empty hole
right through the middle of him.

1140
01:46:07.225 --> 01:46:12.026
He can never kill enough
or steal enough...

1141
01:46:12.096 --> 01:46:14.963
or inflict enough pain
to ever fill it.

1142
01:46:15.033 --> 01:46:17.467
What does he need?

1143
01:46:18.670 --> 01:46:20.604
Revenge.

1144
01:46:23.908 --> 01:46:26.502
For what?

1145
01:46:31.282 --> 01:46:33.216
Bein' born.

1146
01:46:47.065 --> 01:46:49.090
It all happened so fast
with Curly Bill...

1147
01:46:49.167 --> 01:46:51.260
I didn't really have time
to think about it.

1148
01:46:51.336 --> 01:46:53.827
but I've had plenty of time
to think about this.

1149
01:47:01.045 --> 01:47:03.513
I can't beat him. can I?

1150
01:47:05.483 --> 01:47:07.644
No.

1151
01:47:13.691 --> 01:47:17.627
Wait.
I'm goin' with ya.

1152
01:47:23.134 --> 01:47:27.161
Oh. God. I'm sorry.

1153
01:47:27.238 --> 01:47:29.433
I'm sorry. Wyatt.

1154
01:47:29.507 --> 01:47:32.032
It's all right. Doc.

1155
01:47:35.179 --> 01:47:38.114
What's it like to wear
one of those?

1156
01:48:05.576 --> 01:48:07.510
Don't worry.

1157
01:48:07.578 --> 01:48:10.775
They want him.
they gotta come over us first.

1158
01:48:36.908 --> 01:48:41.902
He's waitin' for you by the big oak.
quarter mile up that trail.

1159
01:48:47.452 --> 01:48:50.751
They're not givin' ya
any safe conduct.

1160
01:48:50.822 --> 01:48:55.088
Shootin' starts. you better kick east
to the New Mexico line.

1161
01:48:57.595 --> 01:48:59.859
I ain't got the words.

1162
01:48:59.931 --> 01:49:02.525
I know.

1163
01:49:02.600 --> 01:49:04.932
Me neither.

1164
01:49:12.510 --> 01:49:14.444
Well.

1165
01:49:20.518 --> 01:49:23.722
I didn't think
ya had it in you.

1166
01:49:23.855 --> 01:49:26.756
I'm your huckleberry.

1167
01:49:29.360 --> 01:49:32.261
Why. Johnny Ringo.

1168
01:49:32.330 --> 01:49:36.391
you look like somebody
just walked over your grave.

1169
01:49:37.469 --> 01:49:40.404
Fight's not with you. Holliday.

1170
01:49:40.472 --> 01:49:45.171
I'll beg to differ. sir. We started
a game we never got to finish.

1171
01:49:46.244 --> 01:49:48.610
Play for blood. remember?

1172
01:49:49.848 --> 01:49:53.079
I was just foolin' about.

1173
01:49:54.686 --> 01:49:56.620
I wasn't.

1174
01:49:58.022 --> 01:50:00.217
And this time...

1175
01:50:01.426 --> 01:50:04.020
it's legal.

1176
01:50:11.269 --> 01:50:15.171
All right. lunger.
Let's do it.

1177
01:50:48.606 --> 01:50:50.540
Say when.

1178
01:51:08.893 --> 01:51:12.886
Come on. Come on!

1179
01:51:12.964 --> 01:51:16.127
Oh. Johnny. Come on!

1180
01:51:20.972 --> 01:51:24.499
You're no daisy.
You're no daisy at all!

1181
01:51:25.643 --> 01:51:28.043
Poor soul.

1182
01:51:28.112 --> 01:51:31.013
You were just
too high-strung.

1183
01:51:40.959 --> 01:51:45.987
I'm afraid the strain
was more than he could bear.

1184
01:51:52.837 --> 01:51:57.365
Oh. I wasn't quite
as sick as I made out.

1185
01:51:59.811 --> 01:52:02.371
Good God.

1186
01:52:08.853 --> 01:52:11.754
My hypocrisy
goes only so far.

1187
01:52:16.761 --> 01:52:18.729
All right.

1188
01:52:18.796 --> 01:52:21.287
Let's finish it.

1189
01:52:21.366 --> 01:52:26.702
Indeed. sir. The last charge
of Wyatt Earp and his immortals.

1190
01:53:18.423 --> 01:53:21.358
Hyah! Hyah. come on!

1191
01:53:22.961 --> 01:53:25.896
No! Here!

1192
01:53:25.964 --> 01:53:27.898
Look at this!

1193
01:54:48.379 --> 01:54:50.313
Hello. Wyatt.

1194
01:54:50.381 --> 01:54:53.873
Father Feeney
and I were just...

1195
01:54:53.951 --> 01:54:59.321
investigating the mysteries
of the church of Rome.

1196
01:55:00.424 --> 01:55:05.828
It appears my hypocrisy
knows no bounds.

1197
01:55:05.896 --> 01:55:09.992
You're no hypocrite. Doc.
You just like to sound like one.

1198
01:55:10.067 --> 01:55:12.695
I brought you somethin'.

1199
01:55:18.309 --> 01:55:22.006
Well. let's see.
Where are we today?

1200
01:55:22.079 --> 01:55:25.640
I'm $17 down to you.

1201
01:55:25.716 --> 01:55:29.379
- Two bits a hand. Stud?
- You keep comin' back here.

1202
01:55:29.453 --> 01:55:32.217
I told you not to.
and I meant it.

1203
01:55:32.290 --> 01:55:35.851
You're the only person
I can afford to lose to anymore.

1204
01:55:38.629 --> 01:55:42.121
How we feelin' today. Doc?

1205
01:55:42.199 --> 01:55:44.963
I'm dying. How are you?

1206
01:55:45.036 --> 01:55:47.596
Pretty much the same.

1207
01:55:47.672 --> 01:55:52.234
- So now we add self-pity
to our list of frailties.
- All right. Doc.

1208
01:55:52.310 --> 01:55:55.643
All right. how many
cards you want?

1209
01:55:55.713 --> 01:55:59.012
I don't want
to play anymore.

1210
01:55:59.083 --> 01:56:01.813
How many?

1211
01:56:01.886 --> 01:56:06.914
Damn you.
You're the most fallible.

1212
01:56:06.991 --> 01:56:09.926
stubborn. self-deluded.

1213
01:56:09.994 --> 01:56:13.589
- bullheaded man I've ever
known in my entire life.
- I call.

1214
01:56:14.665 --> 01:56:16.895
- You win.
- Yet with all.

1215
01:56:16.967 --> 01:56:21.529
you're the only human being
in my entire life who ever gave me hope.

1216
01:56:28.179 --> 01:56:31.615
I was in love once.

1217
01:56:32.683 --> 01:56:34.708
My first cousin.

1218
01:56:34.785 --> 01:56:38.243
She was 15.

1219
01:56:40.624 --> 01:56:42.922
We were both so...

1220
01:56:43.994 --> 01:56:46.394
That's good. Doc.

1221
01:56:46.464 --> 01:56:49.160
That's... That's good.
What happened?

1222
01:56:52.303 --> 01:56:55.966
She joined a convent
over the affair.

1223
01:56:56.040 --> 01:56:58.975
She was all I ever wanted.

1224
01:57:00.678 --> 01:57:03.146
What did you want?

1225
01:57:03.214 --> 01:57:06.479
Just to live a normal life.

1226
01:57:06.550 --> 01:57:11.351
There's no normal life. Wyatt.
There's just life.

1227
01:57:11.422 --> 01:57:14.323
Now get on with it.

1228
01:57:14.392 --> 01:57:16.485
Don't know how.

1229
01:57:18.396 --> 01:57:22.162
Sure you do.
Say good-bye to me.

1230
01:57:23.401 --> 01:57:26.063
Go grab
that spirited actress...

1231
01:57:26.137 --> 01:57:29.436
and make her your own.

1232
01:57:29.507 --> 01:57:32.670
Take that beauty and run.
and don't look back.

1233
01:57:32.743 --> 01:57:37.043
Live every second.
Live right up to the hilt.

1234
01:57:37.114 --> 01:57:39.082
Live. Wyatt.

1235
01:57:40.217 --> 01:57:42.276
Live for me.

1236
01:57:43.621 --> 01:57:46.351
Wyatt? If you
ever were my friend.

1237
01:57:46.424 --> 01:57:49.689
if you ever had even
the slightest feelin' for me.

1238
01:57:49.760 --> 01:57:52.251
leave now.

1239
01:57:52.329 --> 01:57:54.320
Leave now.

1240
01:57:58.669 --> 01:58:01.467
Please?

1241
01:58:12.082 --> 01:58:14.812
Thanks for always
bein' there. Doc.

1242
01:58:42.780 --> 01:58:44.805
I'll be damned.

1243
01:58:47.485 --> 01:58:50.420
This is funny.

1244
01:59:09.974 --> 01:59:15.412
I never thought I would see
Gilbert and Sullivan performed
right here in Denver.

1245
01:59:15.479 --> 01:59:18.676
- Good night. Josie.
- Good night.

1246
01:59:18.749 --> 01:59:20.683
Good show.

1247
01:59:37.101 --> 01:59:40.662
Ya ever see the sun come up
over the Rockies?

1248
01:59:40.738 --> 01:59:45.141
It hits all of a sudden.
and below there's California.

1249
01:59:45.209 --> 01:59:48.303
And you swear
you're lookin' at heaven.

1250
01:59:56.153 --> 01:59:58.883
I have nothing left.

1251
01:59:58.956 --> 02:00:01.618
nothing to give you.

1252
02:00:01.692 --> 02:00:06.288
I have no pride.
no dignity.

1253
02:00:06.363 --> 02:00:11.096
No money. I don't even know
how we'll make a living. but...

1254
02:00:14.972 --> 02:00:17.998
I promise I'll love you
the rest of your life.

1255
02:00:33.390 --> 02:00:37.986
Don't worry. Wyatt.
My family's rich.

1256
02:00:44.501 --> 02:00:47.129
What shall we do first?

1257
02:00:47.204 --> 02:00:50.002
What you wanted to do
the first night we met.

1258
02:00:50.074 --> 02:00:52.941
- Remember?
- Uh-uh.

1259
02:00:54.478 --> 02:00:57.845
May I have this dance?

1260
02:00:57.915 --> 02:01:00.008
Yes.

1261
02:01:00.084 --> 02:01:03.019
And then we'll
have room service.

1262
02:01:09.727 --> 02:01:13.390
The power of the Cowboy Gang
was broken forever.

1263
02:01:13.464 --> 02:01:18.231
Ike Clanton was shot
and killed two years later
during an attempted robbery.

1264
02:01:18.302 --> 02:01:23.137
Mattie died of a drug overdose
shortly after she left Tombstone.

1265
02:01:23.207 --> 02:01:26.438
Virgil and Allie Earp
moved to California. where Virgil.

1266
02:01:26.510 --> 02:01:30.139
despite the use of only one arm.
became a town sheriff.

1267
02:01:30.214 --> 02:01:34.173
Wyatt and Josephine
embarked on a series of adventures.

1268
02:01:34.251 --> 02:01:39.553
Up or down. thin or flush.
in 47 years they never left
each other's side.

1269
02:01:39.623 --> 02:01:43.059
Wyatt Earp died
in Los Angeles in 1929.

1270
02:01:43.127 --> 02:01:44.412
Among the pallbearers
at his funeral...

1271
02:01:44.412 --> 02:01:45.970
Among the pallbearers
at his funeral...

1272
02:01:46.046 --> 02:01:50.176
were early Western movie stars
William S. Hart and Tom Mix.

1273
02:01:50.250 --> 02:01:53.219
Tom Mix wept.

